  {name:'Peg\'s Glorified Ham N Eggs',website:'eatatpegs.com',address:'420 S Sierra St',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89501',phone:'(775) 329-2600',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Hawaiian'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Sun":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM"\}',about:'We are a family owned & operated restaurant. We have been voted best breakfast in Reno for 13+ years. In addition to traditional items, we have a variety of breakfast options: skillet breakfasts - our huevos rancheros are one of our most popular dishes, Hawaiian plates - loco moco, teriyaki pork chops & even spam & our benedicts are topped with house-made hollandaise. We also serve a full lunch menu. Peg\'s has something for everyone!',history:'Established in 1999. Family owned and operated.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Two Chicks',website:'twochicksreno.com',address:'752 S Virginia St',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89501',phone:'(775) 323-0600',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM"\}',about:'From the Two Chicks that brought you GourMelt. Two Chicks is committed to serving delicious comfort food with friendly, warm service. We will have all your favorite breakfast items with a modern, creative twist. We use local free range eggs, fresh baked bread, fire-roasted coffee and feature local breweries. We are committed to the "buy local" movement and will procure the freshest ingredients from farms and dairys in our area. All of our food is made with the love and care you would expect from family because that is what you are to us!',history:'Established in 2014. A dream come true for GourMelt owners Jessie and Haley, Two Chicks strives to bring comfort food in a warm and inviting environment. You can find all American breakfast, gluten-free options and GourMelt\'s famous grilled cheese creations as well as a full bar.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Wild River Grille',website:'wildrivergrille.com',address:'17 S Virginia St Ste 180',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89501',phone:'(775) 284-7455',categories: ['American (New)',' Bars',' Steakhouses'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Creative Casual Cuisine. Incredible hand-crafted cocktails.River inspired decor. Fabulous outdoor patio. Located on the RiverWalk in Downtown Reno, Wild River Grille is a contemporary restaurant with nature-inspired influences, a full bar and expansive riverside patio. Situated in the Riverside Artist Lofts Building just across Virginia Street from the Pioneer Theatre, we\'re serving lunch and dinner 7 days a week starting at 11:00 am. Our dining menu features both traditional and innovative cuisine, while our bar prepares incredible hand-crafted cocktails featuring fresh squeezed juices and liquor infusions. Currently featuring our Summer Dinner Concert Series with local musicians playing DAILY!',history:'Established in 2007. The June 2007 grand opening of the Wild River Grille was merely the continuation of decades of dedication to the concept of hospitality. Combining over 50 years of experience, co-founders Chuck Shapiro and Doug Holter had been friends for 15 years before deciding to embark on their joint endeavor. What was created is Reno\'s finest combination of service, food, and spirits delivered in a casual, fun and relaxing environment. Located in the historic Riverside Hotel building, and part of the vibrant Downtown Riverwalk Arts District, the grille celebrates music, art and nature. From the hand-crafted Ponderosa Pine bar and nature inspired dining room, to the expansive riverfront patio complete with bandstand, you will be served delicious creations and treated with genuine warmth. Our dedication to your enjoyment is why the Wild River Grille is now the fastest growing restaurant in Reno.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Great Full Gardens-Midtown',website:'greatfullgardens.com',address:'555 S Virginia St Ste 107',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89501',phone:'(775) 324-2013',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Vegetarian'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"8:00 AM - 8:30 PM","Tue":"8:00 AM - 8:30 PM","Wed":"8:00 AM - 8:30 PM","Thu":"8:00 AM - 8:30 PM","Fri":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM"\}',about:'Great Full Gardens Cafe & Eatery features a wholesome menu for breakfast, lunch & dinner, full barista services, beer & wine in a casual full service environment. Our restaurant caters to both the people with specialized dietary needs, such as vegan, gluten-free or Paleo, as well as to the person just looking for great flavor and a menu that is unique and delicious! We are proud to support and feature many items from local vendors and farmers.',history:'Established in 2008. Opened in March 2013, Great Full Gardens Cafe & Eatery in the beautiful Midtown District features a casual wholesome menu for breakfast, lunch & dinner, full barista services, beer & wine. Our restaurant caters to both the people with specialized dietary needs, such as vegan, gluten-free or Paleo, as well as to the person just looking for great flavor and a menu that is unique and delicious! We are proud to support and feature many items from local vendors, farmers and our very own Great Full Gardens greenhouse.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'The Depot Craft Brewery Distillery',website:'thedepotreno.com',address:'325 E 4th St',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89512',phone:'(775) 737-4330',categories: ['Breweries',' Distilleries',' Gastropubs'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"3:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Our mission at The Depot is to share our pursuit and passion for transforming base ingredients into far more noble forms. Whether creating our spirits, beer or food, we subscribe to the theory that with care and passion, our craft offerings can be greater than the sum of their simple parts. Reaching such lofty goals usually comes from experimentation with a foundation of quality ingredients and process knowledge. Our production spaces were designed with this in mind, allowing our imaginations to run wild and offering endless possibilities to perfect our craft. With an eye toward local sourcing, quality, and the creation of products both traditional and innovative, we tender our goods to our neighbors near and far in the hope to bring an exceptional craft experience.',history:'Established in 2014. Our mission at The Depot is to share our pursuit and passion for transforming base ingredients into far more noble forms. Whether creating our spirits, beer or food, we subscribe to the theory that with care and passion, our craft offerings can be greater than the sum of their simple parts. Reaching such lofty goals usually comes from experimentation with a foundation of quality ingredients and process knowledge. Our production spaces were designed with this in mind, allowing our imaginations to run wild and offering endless possibilities to perfect our craft. With an eye toward local sourcing, quality, and the creation of products both traditional and innovative, we tender our goods to our neighbors near and far in the hope to bring an exceptional craft experience.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'101 Taiwanese Cuisine',website:'101taiwanese.com',address:'400 W 5th St Ste 104',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89503',phone:'(775) 657-6144',categories: ['Chinese',' Taiwanese',' Bubble Tea'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"Closed","Wed":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Boba Milk Tea. Braised Beef Noodle Soup. Spicy Chicken W/ Basil. Taiwanese Handmade Sweet Sausage. Popcorn Chicken (Salty Spicy) Stinky Tofu. Oyster Pancake.',history:'Established in 2012. Open in March 4th 2012.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'The Stone House Cafe',website:'stonehousecafereno.com',address:'1907 S Arlington Ave',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89509',phone:'(775) 284-3895',categories: ['American (New)',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Wine Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"Closed","Wed":"8:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Thu":"8:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Fri":"8:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 8:00 PM"\}',about:'Open Seven days a week serving breakfast till 4pm lunch till 4:30 and dinner and dinner till 9pm except Sundays and Mondays 8pm. We are in a quaint 1920 Rock House located minutes from Downtown, with a cool Rock n Roll Poster collection on the walls and warm colors surround you. Gourmet all day with menu items that will awaken your palate with imagination and flavor. The selection is mind boggling and unique so everyone in your party will find the perfect dish to order. Fresh Fish, Lamb, Steaks, Tapas, Oysters, Burgers, Sandwiches and healthy Salad Entres galore. Breakfast and lunch all day is very popular since we are a 24 hour town. Happy Hour Daily 3pm to 6pm. The outdoor Patio is like being in European garden where each dining area has it\'s own ambiance surrounded by flowers and trees. Truly beautiful',history:'Established in 1876. Paul Abowd original Chef/Owner of Adeles Restaurant in Carson City and Pegs Glorified Ham & Eggs in Reno decided to get back into the kitchen at age 77. Remodeled a historical home and designed the largest European garden patio in Northern Nevada. A quaint three room house with a full service Cafe bar is the setting during the winter months. Patio Bar open in the Summer on Tuesday thru Friday nights with solo guitarist playing from 6-9pm',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Pine State Biscuits - Reno',website:'pinestatebiscuits.com',address:'200 S Center St',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89501',phone:'(775) 432-2464',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Southern',' Comfort Food'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Twisted Fork',website:'twistedforkreno.com',address:'1191 Steamboat Pkwy Ste 1400',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89521',phone:'(775) 853-6033',categories: ['American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"9:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'Putting a twist on the traditional idea of lunch & dinner!',history:'Established in 2011. The Twisted Fork is a modern American cuisine with a twist. We have various influences such as Californian and Latin.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Atlantis Toucan Charlie\'s Buffet & Grille',website:'atlantiscasino.com/dining/fine-dining/tcb',address:'3800 S Virginia St',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89502',phone:'(775) 824-4433',categories: ['Buffets'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 3:00 PM,4:30 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Reimagined and still unrivaled. There\'s a new way to buffet. And here, even the décor is delicious. Featuring live action stations, including Sauté & Grille, Carvery, Charcuterie, Far East, Pho, Sea Fare, Southwest and Specialty Made-to-Order Salads. And when the main course is over, visit Dessert Island, complete with nine flavors of house-made gelato and cotton candy daily.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Golden Flower Vietnamese',website:'goldenflowervietnamese.com',address:'205 W 5th St',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89503',phone:'(775) 323-1628',categories: ['Vietnamese',' Chinese'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"Closed","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Welcome to the Golden Flower! The place to enjoy a good authentic Vietnamese lunch and dinner. We are so glad that you have chosen our restaurant as your choice of pleasure. Keep in mind that each entree is made freshly by every order. We want you to relax and enjoy some home cooking Vietnamese cuisine. It is best that good food is not rushed. If you feel that you don\'t have the time or the patient to wait, please come back another time when it is more convienant for you. Other wise, please sit back and enjoy the atmosphere while we prepare a fantastic meal you\'ll never forget. Our staff is pleased to serve you and we hope that you will be back again. We specialize in Vietnamese food but also serve a large selection of Chinese and Vegetarian food also and accomendate anything to your liking. Sincerely, Golden Flower Management and Staff.',history:'Established in 1992. Been serving the freshest Vietnamese and Chinese food for over 19 years.',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Sushi Pier',website:'sushipier1.com',address:'1290 E Plumb Ln Ste J',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89502',phone:'(775) 825-6776',categories: ['Sushi Bars',' Japanese',' Buffets'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Süp',website:'sup.restaurant',address:'669 S Virginia St',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89501',phone:'(775) 324-4787',categories: ['Sandwiches',' Soup',' Salad'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"Closed"\}',about:'Süp is a family run business. We make all of our soups, stocks, sauces and salad dressings from scratch. We utilize local ingredients and believe in being a big part of the community. We believe in real food, great customer service and a fun environment. We cater to all taste buds and diets including many items that are gluten free, vegetarian and vegan.We serve 6-8 homemade soups per day along with amazing salads, sandwiches and appetizers. We offer an assortment of homemade desserts from Round Bakery along with locally roasted coffee served French press style from The Hub. We also have a great beer and wine menu with lots of unique and delicious choices, including local beers. Come enjoy our beautiful deck in the heart of MidTown District and have a delicious meal just by yourself or with friends and family!',history:'Established in 2007. My name is Kasey, my husband Christian and I opened Süp in August 2007. After many years working in the restaurant industry and opening our own Private chefing business we decided to open a restaurant of our own. We wanted to bring a unique dining option to Reno that focused on homemade soups along with salads and sandwiches. Our love for Reno and the Downtown area brought us to the area now know as MidTown. When we opened, this area was in need of revitalization but we saw the potential and decided to take the risk. We opened our first location with only seven tables! We quickly outgrew the space but worked on developing our menu and building our clientele. In July 2011 we moved to our new and much larger location where we reside today, just a block up the street. We can now accommodate up to 100 people with the beautiful deck seating included. We continue to grow our business and love serving the people of Reno and beyond wonderful, homemade food served with heart!',user: User.find(2)},
  {name:'Ichiban Japanese Steak House',website:'ichibanreno.com',address:'345 N Virginia St',city:'Reno',state:'NV',zipcode:'89501',phone:'(775) 323-5550',categories: ['Japanese',' Steakhouses'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:30 PM - 9:15 PM","Tue":"4:30 PM - 9:15 PM","Wed":"4:30 PM - 9:15 PM","Thu":"4:30 PM - 9:15 PM","Fri":"4:30 PM - 9:15 PM","Sat":"4:30 PM - 9:15 PM","Sun":"4:30 PM - 9:15 PM"\}',about:'"The Best Tasting Show in Town"™ - Ichiban Japanese Steak House has been a local favorite for over 40 years. Enjoy the artistry and showmanship of Teppanyaki/Hibachi, where skilled chefs prepare sizzling entrees right at your table.',history:'Established in 1980. Downtown Reno for 40 years! The Best Tasting Show in Town is located in Eldorado Resort Casino.',user: User.find(2)},
