  {name:'Lazy Dog Restaurant & Bar',website:'lazydogrestaurants.com',address:'1725 Festival Plaza Dr',city:'Las Vegas',state:'NV',zipcode:'89135',phone:'(702) 727-4784',categories: ['American (New)',' Comfort Food',' Burgers'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Tue":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Wed":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Thu":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)"\}',about:'Lazy Dog serves handcrafted American food and drink with seasonally-inspired ingredients. When you walk in, you get a small mountain town vibe from the warm, caring service and the rustic social setting. It\'s a great place to get together with friends and family.',user: User.find(7)},
  {name:'Bobby Q',website:'bobbyqbbq.com',address:'8501 N 27th Ave',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85051',phone:'(602) 995-5982',categories: ['Barbeque',' American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Bobby Q offers a culmination of barbeque favorites. Along with extensive barbecue research mixed with culinary expertise, the secret behind Bobby Q\'s barbeque lies within the slow cooking process over Tennessee hickory wood paired with the perfect blend of spices found in the special dry rub for the meat, as executed by barbeque master, Executive Chef Mark Hittle. This results in succulent hand-pulled pork, smoky sausage links, fork-tender brisket, and ribs that fall right off the bone. Bobby Q is sure to offer barbecue fare unlike any other. The starters will whet your appetite and the desserts will satiate your sweet-tooth cravings, but the barbecue is the show-stopper. Three different ribs are offered (St. Louis, Texas, and baby back) as well as chicken, salmon, burgers, and hand-cut steaks. Nestled in a charmingly-rustic setting, Bobby Q\'s building features reclaimed woodwork with exposed brick walls, antique gas lamps, and 10-foot vintage French doors. Come visit us soon!',history:'Established in 2005. Bobby Q opened in 2005 at the former site of Bobby McGee\'s, offering a culmination of barbeque favorites. Owner Bob Sikora is a true BBQ aficionado, spending more than 10 years researching cooking techniques from the masters across the country.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Cocina Madrigal',website:'cocinamadrigal.com',address:'4044 S 16th St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85040',phone:'(602) 243-9000',categories: ['Salad',' Tacos',' Burgers'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Chef Leo first developed his culinary chops in Mexico as a teenager and has been building kitchens and menus in the valley for the past 30 years. Cocina Madrigal specializes in hand crafted tacos, homemade enchiladas, fresh bold salads and made form scratch specialties. Come check out South Phoenix\'s newest Chef Owned Restaurant.',history:'Established in 2018. We are a brand new restaurant and we just opened last week.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Hash Kitchen Gainey Ranch',website:'hashkitchen.com',address:'8777 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85253',phone:'(623) 324-1914',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Bars',' American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'Hash Kitchen is a creative a.m. eatery with a DJ, glitter mimosas, AZ\'s largest Build-Your-Own Bloody Mary Bar and over-the-top exciting menu items that yield a social dining experience. Guests can expect to see cereal French toast, giant breakfast sandwiches, creative craft cocktails and bold savory dishes among other items. It is designed to be the go-to spot for locals and a culinary destination for visitors.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Joe\'s Farm Grill',website:'joesfarmgrill.com',address:'3000 E Ray Rd Bldg 1',city:'Gilbert',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85296',phone:'(480) 563-4745',categories: ['American (Traditional)',' Pizza',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"7:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"7:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"7:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"7:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"7:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"7:30 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'History 
  Established in 2006. 

  In 1967, the young Jim + Virginia Johnston family built a home on their farm to raise sons Joe, Steve + Paul. The expanses of grass and abundant, mature trees made for a great childhood. As the sons grew and were married, the home was used by the new families. As the family farm gave way to the new Agritopia development (neighborhoods + urban farming), the home was redeveloped into what is now Joe\'s Farm Grill. The architectural vision was to create a retro-futuristic burger stand. Notable touches are the butterfly roof, Jetsonian restrooms, LCD displays, automated condiment station, and a glass box kitchen. The food concept was to take the burger stand menu to the next level and to use as much of the produce grown on the adjacent The Farm at Agritopia (@agritopiafarm) as possible. Since opening, the restaurant has continued to grow, fueled by "Free Cheeseburger Day" every November and being featured on Food Network\'s "Drive-ins, Diners and Dives" with Guy Fieri.',history:'Established in 2006. In 1967, the young Jim + Virginia Johnston family built a home on their farm to raise sons Joe, Steve + Paul. The expanses of grass and abundant, mature trees made for a great childhood. As the sons grew and were married, the home was used by the new families. As the family farm gave way to the new Agritopia development (neighborhoods + urban farming), the home was redeveloped into what is now Joe\'s Farm Grill. The architectural vision was to create a retro-futuristic burger stand. Notable touches are the butterfly roof, Jetsonian restrooms, LCD displays, automated condiment station, and a glass box kitchen. The food concept was to take the burger stand menu to the next level and to use as much of the produce grown on the adjacent The Farm at Agritopia (@agritopiafarm) as possible. Since opening, the restaurant has continued to grow, fueled by "Free Cheeseburger Day" every November and being featured on Food Network\'s "Drive-ins, Diners and Dives" with Guy Fieri.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Pizzeria Bianco',website:'pizzeriabianco.com',address:'623 E Adams St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85004',phone:'(602) 258-8300',categories: ['Pizza',' Salad',' Tapas/Small Plates'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"Closed"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Rehab Burger Therapy',website:'rehabburgertherapy.com',address:'7210 E 2nd St',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 621-5358',categories: ['Burgers',' Bars',' American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Founded on the idea that it\'s actually therapeutic to slow down and celebrate life\'s simple pleasures, Rehab Burger Therapy serves up the treatment you crave in a fun beach environment. Top rated on Yelp and Trip Advisor this relatively new restaurant has enjoyed a fast rise to burger excellence securing 7 Best Burger Awards in just 3 years. A friendly staff and casual setting seals the deal. Located in the heart of old town Scottsdale Rehab boasts a great patio and free WiFi. Walking distance to Scottsdale Center for the Arts, Scottsdale Stadium and tons of quaint shops Rehab is a great place to fuel up before an adventure. Check In at Rehab and benefit from serious hunger remedies including Pig Wings, Cantina TaCODos, Award Winning Burgers, Gnarly Salads, Killer Chicken Wings, Pastas and the famous Pot Brownies dessert. Serious Milkshakes are handmade in a full bar also offering "Speech Therapy" via a refreshing list of mixed drinks, home town brews and even adult milkshakes. The full menu is available on the Rehab\'s mobile friendly website and free Mobile App. Isn\'t it about time you found yourself at Rehab? CHECK IN and taste what the Buzz is all about!',history:'Established in 2011. Rehab Burger Therapy was founded on the belief that everyone deserves a break from the daily grind. A belief that it\'s therapeutic to slow down and celebrate life\'s simple pleasures like the company of friends, good music and a ridiculously delicious meal. Created by three friends that needed some rehabilitation of their own, Rehab Burger Therapy is a story about friends searching for that "good o\'l day\'s vibe" and finding it\'s been right in front of them the whole time. During a BBQ get together in the summer of 2011 the owners Denise, Ken & Wiley were enjoying a rehabilitating day with great food and friends while reminiscing, then it hit em like a fat burger in the face, the whole world could use a little Rehab. So CHECK-IN @ REHAB, sit back, relax and enjoy the benefits of being properly treated.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Hash Kitchen Chandler',website:'hashkitchen.com',address:'2855 W Ray Rd Ste 4',city:'Chandler',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85224',phone:'(623) 324-1640',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Burgers',' Sandwiches'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'Hash Kitchen is a creative a.m. eatery with a DJ, glitter mimosas, AZ\'s largest Build-Your-Own Bloody Mary Bar and over-the-top exciting menu items that yield a social dining experience. Guests can expect to see cereal French toast, giant breakfast sandwiches, creative craft cocktails and bold savory dishes among other items. It is designed to be the go-to spot for locals and a culinary destination for visitors.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Sicilian Butcher',website:'thesicilianbutcher.com',address:'15530 N Tatum Blvd Ste 160',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85032',phone:'(602) 607-0365',categories: ['American (Traditional)',' Italian',' Sandwiches'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:30 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:30 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Craft Meatballs and Charcuterie Boards',history:'Established in 2017. The Sicilian Butcher, Craft Meatballs and Charcuterie Bar, specializes in hand-rolled meatballs with saucy attitude, fresh-made pastas and house-cured meats. The choose-your- own-meatball adventure comes in three steps: pick your balls, pick your sauces and pick your bottoms. For more information, visit online.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Arrogant Butcher',website:'thearrogantbutcher.com',address:'2 E Jefferson Ste 150',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85004',phone:'(602) 324-8502',categories: ['American (Traditional)',' Seafood',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'At The Arrogant Butcher, enjoy a juicy steak or burger with a beer in our bustling downtown Phoenix restaurant and bar. Drop in to impress at a power lunch, share in the timeless class of dinner and a show, or pre-game before the big game. For snackable bar bites to second-to-none seafood from the raw bar, and craft beer to fancy cocktails, The Arrogant Butcher understands that impeccably crafted food is always in style. So come on over - we have your table ready.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Four Peaks Brewing Co.',website:'fourpeaks.com',address:'1340 E 8th St Ste 104',city:'Tempe',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85281',phone:'(480) 303-9967',categories: ['Pubs',' Breweries',' American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"9:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Four Peaks prides itself on its selection of award-winning ales that never fail to satisfy. Their menu of off-the-beaten-path grub keeps people coming back for more. Be sure to stop by for Weekend Brunch at Four Peaks each Saturday and Sunday from 9 AM - 1 PM!',history:'Established in 1996. Located in a 19th Century warehouse that was once home to the Pacific Creamery, Four Peaks Brewery also seems to exude that same charm of an earlier time. Little has been done to alter the look of this Mission Revival style building, and it shows. For more than 15 years, Four Peaks has cultivated quite a following for both beer enthusiasts and folks who crave something a little different from what a traditional chain restaurant has to offer.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Mission Old Town',website:'themissionaz.com',address:'3815 N Brown Ave',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 636-5005',categories: ['Latin American',' Mexican',' Bars'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Made-to-order tableside guacamole, signature margaritas and award-winning almejas al vapor. Grilled and slow-roasted meats and seafood.',history:'Established in 2008. Old Town Scottsdale\'s heart is beating to a Latin drum, now that The Mission has arrived and brightened the restaurant scene. Renowned Zinc Bistro Chef Matt Carter is now cooking up modern Latin cuisine blending influences from Spain, Mexico, Central America and South America. Home made Tortillas, Arepas, and Salsas are made fresh daily and all meats are prepared on a Plancha or a grill using pecan and mesquite wood that instills a rich flavor.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Olive & Ivy',website:'oliveandivyrestaurant.com',address:'7135 E Camelback Rd Ste 195',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 751-2200',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Mediterranean',' Seafood'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Join us in Scottsdale, sit back and relax like royalty as we transport you to the Mediterranean with a menu inspired by timeless elegance. Snack on freshly baked Pain de raisin at brunch, slowly sip sangria on our sunlit patio for lunch or enjoy bruschetta with prosciutto or Manchego for dinner. Seafood dishes full of flavor like our Shrimp Scampi Risotto, and shareable treats like Bacon Wrapped Dates, whisk you away to your own little slice of the French Riviera. Reds from Argentina, whites from Napa Valley, bubbly from France, and craft beers will make happy hour at Olive & Ivy feel like a swig of the good life.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Butters Pancakes & Café - Hayden Rd',website:'butterscafe.com',address:'8300 N Hayden Rd Ste F104',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85258',phone:'(480) 629-4333',categories: ['Cafes',' Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sat":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sun":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM"\}',about:'Recognized for offering Scottsdale\'s finest breakfast and lunch creations all day, from 6:30 a.m to 2:30 p.m., 7-days a week. Fresh, innovative food served consistently with unsurpassed quality by dedicated team members in a clean and warm environment. Famous for their Freshly-Squeezed OJ, Omelettes, Pancakes, Waffles, Crepes, Sandwiches, Burgers, Fresh Salads and full Espresso Bar. Also known for their popular outdoor patio great for people watching.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Little Miss BBQ-University',website:'littlemissbbq.com',address:'4301 E University Dr',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85034',phone:'(602) 437-1177',categories: ['Barbeque',' Sandwiches'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"Closed","Wed":"11:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Sun":"Closed"\}',about:'Little Miss BBQ is built around providing our idea of amazing central Texas style barbecue and to be the best part of your day. We use labor intensive techniques using Arizona white oak, pecan, pistachio and mesquite firewood in smokers that we designed using all of our knowledge about what it takes to create amazing barbecue. We use prime beef sourced from a single rancher who we believe creates the best tasting beef in the US. We then use our technique, simple seasoning and clean burning smokers to try and highlight the amazing beef, pork and turkey to highlight the quality without it getting lost in sauce and crazy flavors. The barbecue is served meat market style which is deli style where you can order as much or as little as you like or for simplicity we offer plates and sandwiches. Our line and service moves a little slower this way but we believe you deserve to see the meat being sliced in front of you by people that want you to get the very best. We love doing what we do and it\'s a crazy passion that we have to put out our best. We hope you love it as much as we do!',history:'Established in 2010. LMB got our start by competing in KCBS competitions in the southwest. We have relatives in Austin, TX and quickly fell in love with places like Franklin Barbecue, John Mueller Meat Company, Smitty\'s, The Salt Lick and many others. Our focus slowly changed from producing some of the the best competition barbecue in the southwest to producing unbelievable tender and juicy barbecued meats with simple seasonings and be leaving the sauce on the side.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Lo-Lo\'s Chicken & Waffles',website:'loloschickenandwaffles.com',address:'1220 S Central Ave',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85003',phone:'(602) 340-1304',categories: ['Southern',' Soul Food',' Waffles'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 6:00 PM"\}',about:'We are a family owned and operated restaurant; offering award winning soul food, amazing service, and a fun atmosphere that is unlike any other in the valley. We have won numerous awards for our juicy, southern fried chicken and delicious melt-in-your-mouth golden brown waffles. We are also well loved for our other scrumptious soul food favorites such as mac & cheese, collard greens, candy sweets, and cornbread just to name a few. Our chicken satisfies the most distinguished appetites and is considered a champion among champions!',history:'Established in 2002. About a young Larry White who, as soon as he could walk and talk, was put to work bussing tables in his grandmother\'s soul food restaurant, Mrs. White\'s Golden Rule Café. The food, the people, the atmosphere...it was contagious, and it wasn\'t long before Larry would start experimenting with his own recipes. Over the next 10 years, Larry ("Lo-Lo" by that point) would tirelessly perfect his now famous fried chicken and homemade waffle recipes.In 2002, the first 1,000 sq. ft. restaurant opened and started to gain traction in the community. Turns out, it would also garner the attention-turned-devotion of folks like Charles Barkley, Shaq, Muhammad Ali and more, turning Phoenix, AZ into an unlikely destination for authentic soul food. Eventually, that small restaurant would give way to a downtown Phoenix location, then Scottsdale, and Gilbert, then the PHX airport...and before long, Lo-Lo\'s would start popping up in lucky locales across the country.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Taco Guild',website:'tacoguild.com',address:'546 E Osborn Rd',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85012',phone:'(602) 264-4143',categories: ['Bars',' Tacos',' Salad'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Cibo',website:'cibophoenix.com',address:'603 N 5th Ave',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85003',phone:'(602) 441-2697',categories: ['Pizza',' Italian',' Sandwiches'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"5:00 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Set in a restored 1913 bungalow, Cibo (pronounced "CHEE-boh") has hardwood floors, exposed brick, a stained-glass panel and a fireplace to set the mood while revitalizing the downtown Phoenix area with beautiful salads, antipasto, artisanal pizzas and housemade fresh pasta. Now offering breakfast Sautrdays and Sundays from 9 am to 2 pm!',history:'Established in 2005. Set in a restored 1913 bungalow, Cibo (pronounced "CHEE-boh") has hardwood floors, exposed brick, a stained-glass panel and a fireplace to set the mood while revitalizing the downtown Phoenix area with beautiful salads, antipasto, artisanal pizzas and housemade fresh pasta.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Lux Central',website:'luxcoffee.com',address:'4400 N Central Ave',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85012',phone:'(602) 327-1396',categories: ['Coffee & Tea',' Bakeries',' Burgers'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"6:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"6:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"6:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"6:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"6:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"6:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Pappadeaux Seafood Kitchen',website:'pappadeaux.com',address:'11051 N Black Canyon Hwy',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85029',phone:'(602) 331-3434',categories: ['Seafood',' Cajun/Creole'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Convivial chain dishing up hearty portions of New Orleans-style seafood, steaks, salads & more.',history:'Established in 1976. H.D. Pappas left Greece in 1897 and traveled to America to pursue his dreams. He brought with him a passion for quality and service that became the benchmark of his success as he opened restaurants throughout Tennessee, Arkansas and Texas. It was this same dedication to quality & service that H.D. passed down to his sons and grandsons. His sons, Pete and Jim, chose a different path than their father and entered the restaurant equipment and supply business. They opened Pappas Refrigeration in 1945. Jim never dreamed that his sons would come full-circle by opening their first restaurant in 1976.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Culinary Dropout',website:'culinarydropout.com',address:'149 S Farmer',city:'Tempe',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85281',phone:'(480) 240-1601',categories: ['American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"10:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'At Culinary Dropout, raise your glass to friends coming together in Tempe. A place where food and music are life. Join us at happy hour for ice cold beer and our famous soft pretzels with provolone fondue. At dinner, a signature cocktail and slow braised 36-hour pork ribs are a perfect pair. While you and your crew enjoy damn good food & drinks, a local band plays live for great vibes. Come hang out and stay a while.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Matt\'s Big Breakfast',website:'mattsbigbreakfast.com',address:'825 N 1st St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85004',phone:'(602) 254-1074',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Salad',' American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Original Breakfast House',website:'originalbreakfasthouse.com',address:'13623 N 32nd St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85032',phone:'(602) 482-2328',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Cafes'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM","Sun":"6:30 AM - 2:00 PM"\}',about:'We specialize in Unique and Original twists on classic diner food. You will find yourself in a 70\'s California beach atmosphere, that serves up intense flavors in the form of unique twists on American comfort food. Menus favorites include our deep fried French toast, topped with fresh seasonal fruit or paired with our chicken fried chicken, a variety of Eggs Benedicts, unique pancake varieties like Tres Leches and Key Lime Pie pancakes, along with waffles and many omelette choices. For lunch we serve Arizona raised grass beef on in house baked brioche buns, specialty sandwiches and a variety of salads. Fresh squeezed (in front of you) orange juice, locally roasted 100% Costa Rican coffee and yummy in house baked goods round out a great meal.',history:'Established in 2013. Prior to opening Original Breakfast House, owner John Stidham operated almost a dozen restaurants in Northern California. Retiring to Phoenix in 2011, he soon discovered that he missed his life\'s work so he hunted out a closed up restaurant in front of a newly rejuvenated shopping center in Northeast Phoenix, THE ROCK at 32nd Street. After negotiating a lease with the partnership of Genesis Church and Alice Cooper\'s Hard Rock Teen Center, the remodeling began. What he ended up with is a modern/70\'s motif, hip breakfast joint that serves up intense flavors in the form of unique twists on American comfort food. The last five years have been great for the OBH. Yelpers have consistently voted us #1 best breakfast/brunch in Phoenix, we are highly rated on Tripadvisor and in 2014 we were voted AZ central\'s readers choice Best Breakfast winner. We all love what we do here at OBH and appreciate the recognition. Please visit us on Facebook, to see whats new.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Harumi Sushi & Sake- Downtown',website:'harumisushiaz.com',address:'114 W Adams St Ste C101/C102',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85003',phone:'(602) 258-0131',categories: ['Japanese',' Sushi Bars',' Seafood'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"12:00 PM - 8:00 PM"\}',about:'We hand select all items on our menu to ensure that our customers receive the freshest ingredients for your sushi and vegan needs. Harumi serves never-been-frozen top grade sashimi shipped by flight, overnight from all around the globe. HARUMI specialize in purple rice AKA \'forbidden rice\' sushi revered in ancient Japan for its healing power and rich nutritional qualities due to high levels in antioxidants, fiber and less sugar and carbs. With deep flavored tones of toasted nuts, at Harumi we serve purple rice sushi with a blend of traditional Japanese Cuisine and a modern twist for flavors fit for diners throughout the World.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'La Santisima',website:'lasantisimagourmet.com',address:'4117 N 16th St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85016',phone:'(602) 254-6330',categories: ['Mexican',' Vegan',' Vegetarian'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM"\}',about:'Here at La Santisima, we aim to deliver everything that is exciting and fresh about Mexican cuisine to the people of Arizona. Our food combines fresh local produce from farms with unique flavors of chipotle chiles, bright green tomatillos, soft Oaxacan cheese, and pillowy flour and corn tortillas from Mexico. Located on 16th street, just North of Indian School Rd, our menu features gourmet tacos, quesas, burritos, seafood, and a fantastic salsa bar filled with homemade salsas. Try our fruit infused horchata and enjoy beer and margaritas from the bar. Stop by for lunch or dinner today!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Diego Pops',website:'diegopops.com',address:'4338 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 970-1007',categories: ['Cocktail Bars',' Tacos'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Tacos + Tequila make our world go \'round. Inspired by taco and tequila-fueled conversations on the beaches of the Yucatan, Diego Pops takes a modern and playful twist on authentic Mexican favorites. Dishes delivered by our kitchen are made fresh and from scratch, including our classic and reimagined tacos, Brussels Sprout Nachos, and creative cocktails. Set within the walls of a historic Southwestern pottery shop, our open kitchen, playful décor, and extended outdoor patio provide for a friendly, fun, laid-back dining experience.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Citizen Public House',website:'citizenpublichouse.com',address:'7111 E 5th Ave Ste E',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 398-4208',categories: ['Gastropubs',' American (New)',' Salad'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Award winning modern comfort food cuisine & craft beverages featuring a variety of barrel-aged and classic cocktails.',history:'Established in 2011. Citizen Public House is an upscale-casual gastropub located in historic downtown Scottsdale.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'SumoMaya',website:'sumomaya.com',address:'6560 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85253',phone:'(480) 397-9520',categories: ['Mexican',' Asian Fusion',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"5:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"10:00 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:00 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Fogo de Chão Brazilian Steakhouse',website:'fogodechao.com',address:'6300 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85253',phone:'(480) 609-8866',categories: ['Brazilian',' Steakhouses'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:30 AM - 10:30 PM","Sat":"11:30 AM - 10:30 PM","Sun":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Fogo de Chão is an internationally-renowned steakhouse from Brazil that allows guests to discover what\'s next at every turn. Founded in Southern Brazil in 1979, Fogo elevates the centuries-old culinary art of churrasco - roasting high-quality cuts of meat over an open flame - into a cultural dining experience of discovery. Please join us in our dining room, in our more casual Bar Fogo, or bring the Fogo Experience to you with Fogo To-Go or Catering. Visit our website to make a reservation or place an order.',history:'Established in 1979. Fogo de Chao is a leading Brazilian steakhouse, or churrascaria, which has specialized in fire-roasting high-quality meats since 1979 utilizing the centuries-old Southern Brazilian cooking technique of churrasco.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Culinary Dropout',website:'culinarydropout.com',address:'7135 E Camelback Rd Ste 125',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 970-1700',categories: ['American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"10:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'At Culinary Dropout, raise your glass to friends coming together in Scottsdale. A place where food and music are life. Join us at happy hour for ice cold beer and our famous soft pretzels with provolone fondue. At dinner, a signature cocktail and slow braised 36-hour pork ribs are a perfect pair. While you and your crew enjoy damn good food & drinks, a local band plays live for great vibes. Come hang out and stay a while.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Chino Bandido',website:'chinobandido.com',address:'310 W Bell Rd',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85023',phone:'(602) 375-3639',categories: ['Mexican'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'DeFalco\'s Italian Eatery, Grocery & Deli',website:'defalcosdeli.com/index.html',address:'2334 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85257',phone:'(480) 990-8660',categories: ['Italian',' Delis',' Sandwiches'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'We are a deli and grocery specializing in imported meats and cheeses, and restaurant offering a wide variety of sandwiches, pasta, and pizza. We have Italian pastries, housemade pizza dough, sauce, sausage, and meatballs, and freshly made pizza and calzones. We also carry imported Italian products, guanciale, pancetta, impastata, 00 flour, a wide selection of pasta cuts, freshly sliced cold cuts, imported Locatelli pecorino romano, parmigiano reggiano, and more!',history:'Established in 1974. The DeFalco family emigrated from Abuzzi Italy, into Toronto Canada, in 1903. Soon after the family moved to the suburbs of Detroit, MI where the OG DeFalco\'s Deli was born. In 1974, John and Dora DeFalco with their son, Jerry, and their daughter-in-law, Judy, moved to Arizona and opened the DeFalco\'s Italian Deli and Grocery you know today.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Henry',website:'thehenryrestaurant.com',address:'4455 E Camelback Rd',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85018',phone:'(602) 429-8020',categories: ['American (New)',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Coffee & Tea'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Follow the arrow to the greatest neighborhood restaurant in Phoenix, a place where you can always count on a warm welcome from baristas, servers and bartenders who know your order by heart. A fusion of industrial and classical influences, our open dining spaces are bursting with charm and energy. Come and go with ease for your morning coffee, enjoy lunch with a colleague, gather the family together for dinner, or treat yourself to a post-work drink at the bar. For craveable eats and downright delicious cocktails, look no further than a place where you\'ll always be among friends, a place that feels like home: The Henry.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Oak',website:'oakoncamelback.com',address:'111 E Camelback Rd',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85012',phone:'(602) 200-8111',categories: ['American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"3:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"3:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"3:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"3:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"10:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'St. Francis Restaurant brings global cuisine to the neighborhood with a focus on farm-fresh, locally sourced ingredients. Weekend brunch offers live music while you enjoy everything from stuffed French toast, gourmet chicken, and waffles to cold brew. Featured on The Food Network, this local eatery provides an ambiance that is both cozy and industrial. House-made bread, gourmet deserts, crispy fried chicken, wood-fired pizzas and so much more. Come in for Happy Hour and enjoy innovative craft cocktails, delicious, global wines, and craft draft beers. There is something for everyone with a wide selection of vegan vegetarian and gluten-free options. Our wine list is fully crafted to complement each dish on our menu and our artisan cocktails are a reflection of the seasons.',history:'Established in 2009. St. Francis is an experience that takes great pride in infusing itself in the neighborhood culture. It is a combination of hospitality, service and passion, evolved from quality-driven, service-oriented, team-based values.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Chelsea\'s Kitchen',website:'chelseaskitchenaz.com',address:'5040 N 40th St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85018',phone:'(602) 957-2555',categories: ['American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"10:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"9:30 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'An Arizona roadhouse constructed of Adobe brick that pays tribute to the majesty of the Arizona desert with two large fireplaces and an iconic patio where mesquite trees create a warm organic canopy. Flavors are big with our famous steak, fish, and vegetarian taco platters served with made-to-order tortillas. Don\'t miss the famous gluten-free jalapeño cheddar cheese cornbread. With no hidden ingredients you can count on tasting quality in every bite. An exciting lineup of tequila and mezcal along with a prickly pear margarita perfectly compliment this lineup of locally focused southwestern cuisine.',history:'Established in 2005. Chelsea\'s Kitchen, an adobe building with a zinc roof on the canal, was envisioned as an Arizona roadhouse serving food that pays tribute to the heritage and history of the area. Sitting on one of the most unique locations in Arizona, Chelsea\'s Kitchen is located on what used to be an old movie studio, built to film Western themed films. Between what are some of Phoenix oldest neighborhoods, it is nature calls for a celebration of the Southwest. The food is clean, simple and follows this history and ideology. No shortcuts on quality of ingredients, portions or preparation are acceptable. The cooking displays the ingredients and techniques of Arizona, Southern California, New Mexico, Texas, Mexico, Spain, Argentina and Peru. Dishes are created daily with fresh and honest ingredients.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Mexicano',website:'themexicano.com',address:'4801 E Cactus Rd',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85032',phone:'(602) 812-2100',categories: ['Tacos',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Bobby Q - Mesa',website:'bobbyqbbq.com/',address:'1610 S Stapley Dr',city:'Mesa',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85204',phone:'(480) 361-7470',categories: ['American (New)',' Barbeque',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM"\}',about:'Bobby Q offers a culmination of barbeque favorites. Along with extensive barbecue research mixed with culinary expertise, the secret behind Bobby Q\'s barbeque lies within the slow cooking process over Tennessee hickory wood paired with the perfect blend of spices found in the special dry rub for the meat, as executed by barbeque master, Executive Chef Mark Hittle. This results in succulent hand-pulled pork, smoky sausage links, fork-tender brisket, and ribs that fall right off the bone. The starters will whet your appetite and the desserts will satiate your sweet-tooth cravings, but the barbecue is the show-stopper. Visit the newest location in Mesa for barbecue fare unlike any other.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Cornish Pasty',website:'cornishpastyco.com',address:'960 W University Dr Ste 103',city:'Tempe',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85281',phone:'(480) 894-6261',categories: ['British',' Pubs'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Snooze, an A.M. Eatery',website:'snoozeeatery.com',address:'2045 E Camelback Rd Ste A17',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85016',phone:'(602) 730-7533',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sat":"6:30 AM - 4:00 PM","Sun":"6:30 AM - 4:00 PM"\}',about:'Most breakfast & brunch restaurants start with the same script: eggs, batter, coffee & a big ol\' griddle. We\'ve found scripts are a lot like pancakes, they\'re best when flipped, so we\'re always looking to turn the best breakfast classics upside-down & on their side. Stop by for delicious pancakes, french toast, benedicts, breakfast burritos, oatmeal, breakfast sandwiches, bacon & more. From paleo to vegetarian & vegan or dairy free & gluten free friendly, we\'ll happily accommodate food allergies & diets. We want each morning to feel like your weekend & happy hour rolled into one, so our restaurants feature a full bar with alcoholic beverages. From mimosas to bloody marys, margaritas & local craft beers, we\'ve got cocktails & brews covered.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Steak 44',website:'steak44.com',address:'5101 N 44th St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85018',phone:'(602) 271-4400',categories: ['Steakhouses',' Seafood',' Bars'],price:'$$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"4:00 PM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"4:00 PM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Steak 44 specializes in providing a fantastic experience and exceptional personal service. We feature USDA Prime Grade Beef, the highest grade Domestic Wagyu, fresh seafood, a menu of unique side dishes and appetizers, along with an award-winning wine list and great cocktails. Upon your arrival at our steakhouse in the heart of Phoenix, you will be welcomed by an attentive service staff who will see that you have an unforgettable evening. You\'ll walk through our 3,000-bottle wine vault as you enter the fine dining area and be seated in one of many unique nooks on the dining room floor.',history:'Established in 2014. Our guests will be treated to an unforgettable experience from the time they walk through our 3,000-bottle wine vault in the entryway to the moment the dessert plates are cleared from their table and our fresh home made chocolate chip cookies arrive as a thank you for joining us. We have a number of dining areas that will appeal to diners looking for an intimate, romantic setting or larger groups hosting friends and family. Guests seeking a high-energy night out will be drawn to our vibrant bar that features several dining tables or one of our dining areas overlooking all of the action. Those seeking a more private and intimate fine dining experience will love our patio with a fireplace or one of our dining suites with a view of our floor-to-ceiling glassed in exhibition kitchen. No matter what occasion you enjoy at Steak 44, our attentive staff will be focused on making your experience enjoyable and memorable.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Joyride Taco House',website:'joyridetacohouse.com',address:'302 N Gilbert Rd',city:'Gilbert',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85234',phone:'(480) 632-8226',categories: ['Tacos',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Vibrant, modern Mexican made with oh-so-fresh ingredients and kicked-back vibes. Swing in for Taco Tuesday to sip on a sublimely delicious margarita for only 5 bucks. Can we get a shhheeelll yeah? Call or click today to learn more!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Clever Koi',website:'thecleverkoi.com',address:'4236 N Central Ave Ste 100',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85012',phone:'(602) 222-3474',categories: ['Asian Fusion',' Ramen',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Clever Koi is an Asian-inspired kitchen & craft cocktail bar with locations in Central Phoenix and historic downtown Gilbert. Our staff is among the Valley\'s most knowledgeable and energetic, focused on making your experience unique. Our service mantra is seamless hospitality at every turn. Enjoy the sights, sounds and aromas of the open kitchen\'s wood-fired grill and roaring woks. Guests can get a front row seat to staff diligently preparing an ever-evolving menu of steamed buns, house made dumplings, progressive noodle dishes & small plates that reflect flavors and techniques from regions such as Thailand, Korea, China, Vietnam, Japan, and Indo-China. Don\'t miss daily happy hour featuring an eclectic beer, wine & sake list.',history:'Established in 2013. { Best of Phoenix 2014 Awards } Best New School Cocktails & Best Day Off Dinner { Phoenix Magazine Best New Restaurants } { AZ Foothills Best Asian Restaurant 2014 }',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Breakfast Club- Scottsdale',website:'breakfastclub.us',address:'4400 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 222-2582',categories: ['American (Traditional)',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Coffee & Tea'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"6:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"6:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"6:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"6:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'Breakfast Club evolved to break the mold of the typical formica laden, economically driven breakfast engagements saturating the marketplace. We\'ve combined the coolness and community of a coffee shop, with the fresh and wholesome ingredients found at your local farmers market, to give breakfast the makeover it deserves! Breakfast has become the new happy hour',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Arizona Wilderness Brewing',website:'azwbeer.com',address:'721 N Arizona Ave',city:'Gilbert',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85233',phone:'(480) 497-2739',categories: ['Breweries',' Burgers'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Beer and food infused with Arizona.',history:'Established in 2013. For years we dreamed of bringing together our two loves: the beautiful and diverse state of Arizona and with hand crafted, artisanal ales. While backpacking the wondrous depths of our state, we forged ideas that would one day become Arizona Wilderness Brewing Co. Well, here we are! We will continue our endeavor into the remote beauties of both the Arizona Wilderness and Craft Beer. Our belief is that beer is more than a beverage to guzzle on Sundays, more than just another beverage at the party, and more than that cheap yellow fizzy stuff dad drank while wearing his dirty flannel shirts. Beer is culture, and we have a true passion for it! Check out our food menu, as it was created to pair quite nicely with our fine ales. Visit and see what we\'re up to next.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Parlor',website:'theparlor.us',address:'1916 E Camelback Rd',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85016',phone:'(602) 248-2480',categories: ['Pizza',' Italian',' Salad'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'A rustic Italian eatery specializing in wood fired pizzas, handmade pastas, craft cocktails, and an inspired wine and beer list. Our menu is seasonal and always reflects the best local produce arizona growers have to offer.',history:'Established in 2009. a wood oven and a simple vision for a rustic italian eatery is where it all began. that foundation and a long, creative journey has lead us to where we are today. our commitments to craft, value, freshness, and environment have successfully propelled the parlor forward through each changing season, and each passing year. this building originally housed the salon de venus -- a mecca for bobs, beehives, and nearly six decades worth of "cutting edge" hair styles and spa treatments. the owners of the salon decided to hang up the sheers in 2007. through some luck and good fortune, the mei family was able to take over the space and begin dreaming up the parlor. during the massive renovation, a large portion of the old building was demolished and repurposed into all of the wood elements you see around the room, including the dining tables. the salon de venus lives on in the new and sustainably built interiors.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Paradise Valley Burger',website:'paradisevalleyburgercompany.com',address:'4001 E Bell Rd Ste 102',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85032',phone:'(602) 535-4930',categories: ['Burgers',' American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM"\}',about:'BURGERS. Being the best at cooking them. Milkshakes. Being the best at blending them. We love you.',history:'Established in 2011. Diners drive ins and dives. Man vs food!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Rustler\'s Rooste',website:'rustlersrooste.com',address:'8383 S 48th St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85044',phone:'(602) 431-6474',categories: ['Steakhouses'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"4:30 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"4:30 PM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Rustler\'s Rooste serves the finest steaks, ribs, chicken and the freshest seafood. Appetizers are different and delicious. (Yup, we\'ve got rattlesnake).Our desserts will tempt you. We have above standard liquors and wines, and, of course, a variety of your favorite beers. Ask about our Cowboy Stuff -- dinner served family style that includes shrimp, BBQ chicken, beans, swordfish, baked potatoes, seasonal fruit, pork ribs, corn-on-the-cob, sirloin steak strips, fresh raw vegetables and rolls with butter and honey. Better come hungry. Rustler\'s Rooste has live country western music 7 nights a week. Our General Store (for those cool souvenirs) is open nightly 5:00-10:00 PM. Valet parking is available at no charge. The spectacular view and friendly atmosphere is also free. Rustler\'s Rooste begins dinner service at 5:00 PM daily. The lounge opens at 4:00 PM. Happy Hour from 4:00 to 6:00, Monday thru Friday). We are dedicated to our guests 365 days a year.',history:'Established in 1971. Rustler\'s Rooste was established in 1971. The legend goes that the original site, atop a butte in the foothills of South Mountain, was a hideout for cattle rustlers. Today, it is Arizona\'s Legendary Cowboy Steakhouse. It is located 15 minutes from downtown Phoenix and Tempe, 20 minutes from Scottsdale and 10 minutes from the airport. Rustler\'s Rooste is a 2-story building with our lounge on the top levelStroll over the indoor waterfall and take the slide into the dining room.(for the faint of heart, there is a staircase). Both areas are bordered on the north side by large plate glass windows that provide an unparalleled view of the city lights.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Gen Korean BBQ House',website:'genkoreanbbq.com',address:'2000 E Rio Salado Pkwy Ste 1056',city:'Tempe',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85281',phone:'(480) 939-2650',categories: ['Korean',' Barbeque',' Seafood'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:30 AM - 10:30 PM","Tue":"11:30 AM - 10:30 PM","Wed":"11:30 AM - 10:30 PM","Thu":"11:30 AM - 10:30 PM","Fri":"11:30 AM - 11:30 PM","Sat":"11:30 AM - 11:30 PM","Sun":"11:30 AM - 11:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Liberty Market',website:'libertymarket.com',address:'230 N Gilbert Rd',city:'Gilbert',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85234',phone:'(480) 892-1900',categories: ['American (New)',' Coffee & Tea',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'We are a full service, new American restaurant open breakfast, lunch and dinner. American and Mexican breakfast classics with a twist ( some available all day), creative entrees, wood-fired pizza, freshly tossed salads, bountiful sandwiches, natural beef burgers, rustic pasta dishes, desserts+baked goods from our in-house bakery. Our new social counter features full bar, exceptional barista-made espresso drinks and a great selection of beer and wine.',history:'Established in 2008. Liberty Market has existed in the present location since 1935. It was expanded in 1958 with a new storefront and signage -- the storefront and signage you see today. In 2008, we (the fourth owners) expanded and renovated the building. We have exposed the structure of the building and enhanced it with contemporary touches using natural materials. The result is a comfortable, urban meeting place for the community of Gilbert.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Barrio Café',website:'barriocafe.com',address:'2814 N 16th St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85006',phone:'(602) 636-0240',categories: ['Mexican',' Cafes'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Snooze, an A.M. Eatery',website:'snoozeeatery.com',address:'615 S College Ave Suite 103 & 104 Ste 103 & 104',city:'Tempe',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85281',phone:'(602) 704-1256',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sat":"6:30 AM - 4:00 PM","Sun":"6:30 AM - 4:00 PM"\}',about:'Most breakfast & brunch restaurants start with the same script: eggs, batter, coffee & a big ol\' griddle. We\'ve found scripts are a lot like pancakes, they\'re best when flipped, so we\'re always looking to turn the best breakfast classics upside-down & on their side. Stop by for delicious pancakes, french toast, benedicts, breakfast burritos, oatmeal, breakfast sandwiches, bacon & more. From paleo to vegetarian & vegan or dairy free & gluten free friendly, we\'ll happily accommodate food allergies & diets. We want each morning to feel like your weekend & happy hour rolled into one, so our restaurants feature a full bar with alcoholic beverages. From mimosas to bloody marys, margaritas & local craft beers, we\'ve got cocktails & brews covered.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Sicilian Butcher - Chandler',website:'thesicilianbutcher.com',address:'3151 W Frye Rd',city:'Chandler',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85226',phone:'(602) 969-6456',categories: ['Italian',' Cocktail Bars',' Sandwiches'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:30 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:30 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Windsor',website:'windsoraz.com',address:'5223 N Central Ave',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85012',phone:'(602) 279-1111',categories: ['American (New)',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Located in its namesake historic neighborhood, Windsor offers mouthwatering prohibition cocktails and familiar bar food with an upscale twist - the perfect mix of luxe and leisure. Call or click today to learn more!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Buck & Rider',website:'buckandrider.com',address:'4225 E Camelback Rd',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85018',phone:'(602) 346-0110',categories: ['Seafood',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Live/Raw Food'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Impeccable ingredients speak for themselves. We go the distance to source our seafood, meats, and produce directly from fishers and farmers who share our commitment to quality, transparency, and sustainable practices. Our guiding philosophy is simple: superior ingredients, perfectly executed. We fly in the freshest seafood from around the world – seven days a week. That daily catch leaves the airport in our Buck & Rider refrigerated van, headed straight for our kitchens and raw bars. The logistics may be complex, but the mission is straightforward. We do whatever it takes to serve the finest just-caught fish and shellfish of the East, West, and Gulf coasts and beyond. We’ve made Buck & Rider a home away from home, a spot that’s equally welcoming for cocktails and hand-rolled sushi at happy hour, a romantic date night, or brunch and bloodies with friends on the patio. We’re always happy to have you. Our spaces feature an easy flow between indoor and outdoor areas, allowing guests to relax in the glow of the patio’s stone fireplace or a stylish banquette in the dining room. Every aesthetic element, from building materials to lighting, is considered to create a welcoming atmosphere that reflects our philosophy of simplicity and quality. The emphasis on locality in our menu extends to architecture and design, which are unique for every Buck & Rider location, drawing inspiration from the surrounding environment.',history:'Established in 2015. Our team goes to extraordinary lengths to bring you the best ingredients. We take a mindful approach to sourcing buying directly from small producers around the world who engage in sustainable fishing and oyster farming practices. We fly their catch into our kitchens every day. That means hand-picked Louisiana blue crab for our famous crab cakes and Ora King salmon in our sushi. The daily raw bar menu is time-stamped and continuously updated to reflect the freshness of our fish and availability of oysters from our fishermen and farmers. Our commitment to quality goes far beyond seafood. Steaks come from our special Buck & Rider Reserve beef program: USDA certified, aged, and cut to our specifications. Our cocktails follow the same ingredient-driven philosophy, made with hand-squeezed juices and premium spirits. Here, no fussy preparations, no stuffy atmosphere—just an inviting spot to enjoy the best our fishers and farmers have to offer, procured, prepared, and presented with care,',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Toca Madera - Scottsdale',website:'tocamadera.com',address:'4736 N Goldwater Blvd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 930-4357',categories: ['Mexican',' Cocktail Bars',' Steakhouses'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:00 PM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"4:00 PM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"4:00 PM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"4:00 PM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"4:00 PM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM"\}',about:'Now open nightly for dinner and weekend brunch on Saturdays and Sundays 11am-3pm! Toca Madera is a highly acclaimed modern Mexican Steakhouse known for its bold flavors and high quality, sustainable, and organic ingredients.',history:'Established in 2019. First opened in West Hollywood in 2015, Toca Madera reimagines traditional Mexican cuisine, pairing locally sourced ingredients with bold flavors to offer an array of options for every eater. Its diverse menu is designed to offer something for everyone, with vegan, vegetarian, pescatarian and gluten-free choices. Toca Madera restaurants feature a dynamic farm-to-glass cocktail program using fresh, seasonal ingredients, and offers a versatile selection of the finest tequilas and mezcals, as well as a rotating selection of wines from across the globe.',user: User.find(1)},
