  {name:'SanTan Brewing Company',website:'santanbrewing.com',address:'8 S San Marcos Pl',city:'Chandler',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85225',phone:'(480) 917-8700',categories: ['Brewpubs',' Pubs',' American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"9:00 AM - 11:00 PM"\}',about:'In addition to our core beers on draught year round, Brewmaster Anthony Canecchia keeps things exciting for SanTan fans by releasing seasonal, specialty, collaboration + small batch brews. Nothing goes better with great beer than delicious food and we are proud to feature menu selections crafted from scratch daily.',history:'Established in 2007. In 2007, SanTan Brewing Company was born in Historic Downtown Chandler, Arizona in the old Valley National Bank Building. Brewmaster and Founder Anthony Canecchia had a mission... and SanTan Brewing was created and dedicated to the culture of Craft Beer paired with Craft Food to be enjoyed with the art of Conversation. Our belief is that Great Craft Beer and Great Craft Food can be the inspiration for the conversations that can change the world!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Hash Kitchen North Scottsdale',website:'hashkitchen.com',address:'14838 N Frank Lloyd Wright Blvd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85260',phone:'(623) 324-1912',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'Hash Kitchen is a creative a.m. eatery with a DJ, glitter mimosas, AZ\'s largest Build-Your-Own Bloody Mary Bar and over-the-top exciting menu items that yield a social dining experience. Guests can expect to see cereal French toast, giant breakfast sandwiches, creative craft cocktails and bold savory dishes among other items. It is designed to be the go-to spot for locals and a culinary destination for visitors.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Backyard Taco',website:'backyardtaco.com',address:'1524 E University',city:'Mesa',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85203',phone:'(480) 464-8226',categories: ['Mexican'],price:'$',hours:'\{"Mon":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"10:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"10:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"Closed"\}',about:'Our recipe for success is always fresh ingredients and our mesquite grill. It\'s a combo that gives us the authentic taste of Tacos al Carbon. We keep our menu simple because we only offer what we do best.',history:'Established in 2013. Hailing from magical Mazatlan, Mexico, Ruben and Maricela know something about Tacos al Carbon. They started grilling for their family and neighbors in 2005. Word spread and more and more people came as the legend of their tasty tacos grew. Soon people started following them to stranger\'s backyards just to get some of the delicious food off the grill.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Joyride Taco House',website:'joyridetacohouse.com',address:'5202 N Central Ave',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85012',phone:'(602) 274-8226',categories: ['Tacos',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Vibrant, modern Mexican made with oh-so-fresh ingredients and kicked-back vibes. Swing in for Taco Tuesday to sip on a sublimely delicious margarita for only 5 bucks. Can we get a shhheeelll yeah? Call or click today to learn more!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Zu Izakaya',website:'zuizakaya.com',address:'2210 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Tempe',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85281',phone:'(480) 625-4372',categories: ['Sushi Bars',' Izakaya'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Tue":"4:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Wed":"4:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Thu":"4:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Fri":"4:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"4:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'An Izakaya (居酒屋) is a type of informal Japanese drinking establishment that serves small food to accompany the drinks such as sake, and beer. Simply, Izakaya is like a Japanese version of a tapas bar. It\'s a bar that serves a lot of food. The best way to eat in an izakaya is to go with a group of people, so you can sample lots of dishes. Zu Izakaya Asian Kitchen Bar is casual place for after-work drinking.',history:'Established in 2015. Zu Izakaya is type of Japanese gastropub serving with tapas, sushi, hotpot, yakitori, and grill in restaurant.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'SOL Mexican Cocina',website:'solcocina.com',address:'15323 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85254',phone:'(480) 245-6708',categories: ['Mexican',' Bars',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Our restaurants are inspired by the best of coastal Baja California: Warm, welcoming, friendly, inspired by old and new Mexican design. SOL\'s kitchens feature our unique spin on fresh, healthy, coastal Mexican food, lovingly made from scratch.',history:'Established in 2009. Our restaurants are inspired by the best of coastal Baja California: Warm, welcoming, friendly, inspired by old and new Mexican design. SOL\'s kitchens feature our unique spin on fresh, healthy, coastal Mexican food, lovingly made from scratch. Find us in Newport Beach, California; Scottsdale, Arizona; Playa Vista, California; and Denver, Colorado.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Thumb BBQ',website:'thethumb.com',address:'9393 E Bell Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85260',phone:'(623) 324-1795',categories: ['Barbeque',' Burgers',' Bakeries'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 7:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 7:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 7:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 7:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 7:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 7:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 7:00 PM"\}',about:'We are Scottsdale\'s gourmet BBQ gas station, car wash, that was featured on Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives, NBC, ABC, CBS ,The List, and everywhere in between. Guy Fieri calls us "the funky gas station/BBQ cafe dishin\' out da bomb brisket"! While you’re here, visit, our first class car wash and detail service center. Grab some fresh baked goods, and browse our gift shop and visit our wine section. Bring the whole family. There’s nothing like it.',history:'Established in 2012. Locally owned and operated, our Award-Winning BBQ Bistro and Car Wash are worth the trip. We make the ordinary - extraordinary!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The White Chocolate Grill',website:'whitechocolategrill.com',address:'7000 E Mayo Blvd',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85054',phone:'(480) 563-3377',categories: ['American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'The White Chocolate Grill is a contemporary American restaurant. The White Chocolate Grill has a diverse menu of classic American fare; made from scratch using only the highest quality ingredients. A selection of house-made white chocolate and other desserts complement this offering and are proudly served in a unique team-service format assuring friendliness and efficiency. The restaurant is designed with rich wood and real stone which creates an upscale, Frank Lloyd Wright inspired atmosphere. From the leather booth seating, soft lighting and spectacular bar, every element of the design evokes a classic yet sophisticated setting.',history:'Established in 2005. Slatebridge Restaurant Group was founded in 1998 with the idea of building unique restaurants for specific premium restaurant markets. Fourteen years later, Slatebridge is a 600-person team serving five distinct markets across three brands. We operate under a simple vision; the world does not need more restaurants, the world needs more great restaurants. Learn about our brands above or contact us if we can be of service to you.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'True Food Kitchen',website:'order.truefoodkitchen.com',address:'15191 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85254',phone:'(480) 265-4500',categories: ['American (New)',' Vegetarian',' Vegan'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'True Food Kitchen is a restaurant and lifestyle brand inspired by the philosophy that food should make you feel better, and that great tasting food and thoughtfully crafted beverages can serve as the foundation for a life well lived. True Food\'s seasonal menu is guided by the principles of Dr. Andrew Weil\'s anti-inflammatory food pyramid and emphasizes wholesome, simple ingredients with simple preparations to highlight the natural health benefits and flavors of each ingredient. From nutrient-dense staples and carefully sourced proteins to little-known superfoods, True Food Kitchen is committed to sourcing the most responsible, creative, in-season ingredients.',history:'Established in 2008. Founded in Phoenix, Arizona, in 2008, True Food Kitchen is a restaurant and lifestyle brand inspired by the philosophy that food should make you feel better, not worse, and that great tasting food and thoughtfully crafted beverages can serve as the foundation for a life well lived. True Food Kitchen emphasizes wholesome, simple ingredients with simple preparations to highlight the natural health benefits and flavors of each ingredient.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Butterfield\'s Pancake House',website:'butterfieldsrestaurant.com',address:'7388 E Shea Blvd',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85260',phone:'(480) 951-6002',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Juice Bars & Smoothies'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sat":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sun":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM"\}',about:'Fresh-Squeezed OJ, Smoothies, Strong Rich Coffee, Oven Baked Pancakes, French Toast, Belgian Waffles, French Crepes, Moist & Fluffy Omelettes, Scramblers, Original Skillets, Benedicts, Heart-Healthy Selections, Children\'s Menu, Signature Sandwiches, Hot Panins & Wraps, and Salads!',history:'Established in 2005. Serving Scottsdale\'s favorite breakfast since 2005. Famous for their fresh-squeezed OJ, fluffy scratch-made pancakes, crunchy waffles, large moist omelettes, crispy thick-cut bacon and other traditional and creative breakfast and lunch specialties done exceedingly well. Known for offering the finest service and using only the freshest available ingredients.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Postino Arcadia',website:'postinowinecafe.com',address:'3939 E Campbell Ave Ste 100',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85018',phone:'(602) 852-3939',categories: ['Wine Bars',' Italian',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'An industrial winecafé offering unique and approachable wines, simply scrumptious food prepared with local ingredients, and a warm, edgy culture that brings people together. Call or click today to learn more!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Joe\'s Real BBQ',website:'joesrealbbq.com',address:'301 N Gilbert',city:'Gilbert',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85234',phone:'(480) 503-3805',categories: ['Barbeque'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Barbeque is our specialty. We use only pecan wood -- no gas or electric ovens. All of our meats are dry rubbed and cooked VERY SLOWLY using smoke and mild heat. This results in tender, flavorful meat. Joe\'s personal favorite is the turkey, but the biggest sellers are the beef brisket and pulled pork. Our pork ribs are superb, as well. All of our side dishes are made in-house. We peel whole cases of apples for our applesauce, make rich cheese sauce for our mac n\' cheese ... whatever it takes to make the sides special. Our biggest sellers include bbq pit beans, cheesy potatoes, and over-the-top mac n\' cheese. Giant baked potatoes (+1 pound) are a big hit. Available with all of the fixings or topped with one of our smoked meats, they are certainly a meal in themselves. Non-alcoholic beverages include a wide range of bottled sodas, but the stand-out is our homemade root beer. It is also available as a root beer float. A nice selection of beer, wine and cocktails is also available. Desserts are homemade: sweet/tart lemon cake, root beer cake, chocolate chip cookies and peach cobbler.',history:'Established in 1998. On January 20, 1998, Joe\'s Real BBQ opened for business. On our first day, we served over 1,000 customers and business stayed very strong. We were all scrambling and tired, but were able to slowly get organized and stabilize the business. Since that time, we have tried to be true to the motto of Joe\'s Real BBQ, which is "Clean, Delicious, Friendly and Quick." There have been a few changes over time - the original "retail market" became an ice cream stand and, later, additional seating, while an additional covered patio was added to the north. A third Oyler pit was added to meet increased volume. We added locally sourced braised greens and other vegetarian options in 2019. Beer, wine and cocktails made their debut as well. Joe\'s continues to be a family owned and operated restaurant. We all live in Gilbert and are proud to be able to be a part of this growing community.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Green New American Vegetarian',website:'greenvegetarian.com',address:'2240 N Scottsdale Rd',city:'Tempe',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85281',phone:'(480) 941-9003',categories: ['Vegetarian',' Vegan',' Gluten-Free'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"Closed"\}',about:'green New American Vegetarian is a restaurant for everyone, not just vegans & vegetarians. Chef Damon hopes to open the hearts and minds of meat eaters everywhere! This location also offers a daily vegan taco menu with a revolving Chameleon ever changing taco special weekly.',history:'Established in 2006. "My grandfather and great grandfather built a house next to a lake. This was the house where I learned to cook. I was seven years old when my grandmother told me to go into the woods to pick fresh dandelion greens for her salad. This was where my hands first smelled of fresh garlic. Where the scent of baking bread intoxicated my senses and the hand rolled pasta made my mouth water. This is where I took the tomato off the vine and placed it into the pot and where we picked the cherries from the tree for the cherry pies that made the neighbors swoon to my grandparents\' house. This is where I fell in love with the asparagus and the artichoke and the arugula. This is where I learned to celebrate food. This is why I cook for you. And this is why I am Green." -- Chef Damon Brasch',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Hula\'s Modern Tiki',website:'hulasmoderntiki.com',address:'5114 N 7th St',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85014',phone:'(602) 265-8454',categories: ['Hawaiian',' Caribbean',' Tiki Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"10:30 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:30 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'HULA\'S serves modern, island cuisine at a great value in a relaxed, casual atmosphere. We specialize in fresh, seasonal fish flown in from Hawaii daily, prepared a variety of ways, including (when available) Blackened Ahi tuna with wasabi mash potatoes, Macadamian nut encrusted Butterfish and Pan Fried Mahi with wok seared shiitake mushrooms. Our starters include favorites such as seared ahi wontons with wasabi cream sauce, fresh, lightly marinated poke and classic ahi loin sashimi. You can jump into a basket of our crispy sweet potato fries (with our signature fresh ginger Hula Sauce for dipping), or try the crispy coconut shrimp rolls; stuffed with succulent shrimp cooked to perfection with Thai basil and sprinkled with toasted coconut. And, don\'t forget our signature Duke\'s Luau Pork, available as a plate with our island slaw & sticky rice, or as the pork sandwich on our artisan buns, as well as South Seas fish tacos, Bali Hai Ribs and the Spicy Thai Chicken Bowl.',history:'Established in 2009. HULA\'S Modern Tiki was started in September of 2009 by Phoenician M. Dana Mule\', and brothers Chris & Craig Delaney of Monterey, CA (via Long Island, NY & Maui, HI). As a frequent business traveler to Monterey, Dana originally fell in love with HULA\'S Island Grill & Tiki Room in \'00. In February of \'06 he approached Chris & Craig and began the process of bringing HULA\'S to Phoenix. The partner\'s spent more than a year searching the entire Valley for the perfect location, and in August of \'08, stumbled upon the old, hexagonal windowed, peak roofed building at 4700 N. Central Ave. Not only did the original A-frame design of the building lend itself to the Polynesian theme, but the community exuded the kind of character, diversity and soul that they were all looking for. This incarnation of HULA\'S is completely unique, and reflects the urban renewal of the Central corridor. The goal was to accentuate the classic architecture, while always paying homage to HULA\'S tiki roots.',user: User.find(1)},
