  {name:'Roaring Fork',website:'roaringfork.com',address:'4800 N Scottsdale Rd Ste 1700',city:'Scottsdale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85251',phone:'(480) 947-0795',categories: ['American (Traditional)',' Bars',' Steakhouses'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'The Perch Brewery',website:'perchpubbrewery.com',address:'232 S Wall St',city:'Chandler',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85225',phone:'(480) 773-7688',categories: ['Gastropubs',' Breweries',' Pubs'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"9:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'The Perch Brewery and Pub is located in Historic Downtown Chandler Arizona. It is not only a Brewery and Pub, but home to a collection of brightly colored, tropical rescue birds. We feature 30 craft beers on tap, and an ever changing selection of Perch beers. Our Brewmaster Bucky is responsible for our innovative beers. Chef Rene Vargas thoughtfully prepares Craft Food, his house specialties incorporate Perch and other craft beers into their ingredients. If beer isn\'t your thing enjoy one of our inspired craft cocktails, and a full bar.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Federal Pizza',website:'federalpizza.com',address:'5210 N Central Ave Ste 104',city:'Phoenix',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85012',phone:'(602) 795-2520',categories: ['Pizza',' Italian',' Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Housed inside a 1950s Federal Bank building, this mid-century gem is a cozy-cool spot for any occasion. Post up at the bar to enjoy an old-school wine cooler or swing through what once was the bank\'s drive-thru lane to grab a growler of craft beer and wood-fired pizza to go!',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Yard House',website:'yardhouse.com',address:'9401 W Westgate Blvd Bldg F',city:'Glendale',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85305',phone:'(623) 872-3900',categories: ['Bars',' Vegetarian',' American (New)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Tue":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Wed":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Thu":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Fri":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)"\}',about:'Yard House, the modern American gathering place where beer and food lovers unite, is an upscale, casual eatery known for great food, classic rock music, an energetic vibe and endless fleet of tap handles featuring the best American craft and import beers. Each Yard House location offers 100+ draft brews along with an array of craft cocktails. Beer is our passion, which means we\'re always staying on top of the latest and greatest brews from around the corner and around the world. At any given moment, we have 3,000 gallons of beer flowing through our keg room to 100+ taps at our center-island bar. We also have a rotating Chalkboard Series featuring unique and complex beers from local, domestic and import brewers. Our globally inspired menu features more than 100 made-from-scratch favorites, from signature starters like Poke Nachos and Fried Mac + Cheese, to street tacos, grilled burgers, pizza, seafood and steak. Each Yard House has a distinct vibe with original artwork, a hand-picked playlist of 10,000 classic songs, and glass-enclosed keg room housing up to 3,000 gallons of fresh, quality beer. Founded in Long Beach, Calif., in 1996, Yard House now spans across the U.S. with over 75 locations and is open daily for lunch, dinner, happy hour and late-night dining.',history:'Established in 1996. When the craft beer revolution started 21 years ago, Yard House had a vision - to create the largest draft beer system in the world. We took our experience with brews and breweries and coupled it with a kitchen that creates culinary innovations to be enjoyed in an energetic atmosphere.The restaurant\'s name was derived from an early Colonial tradition of serving 36-inch tall glasses - or yards - to weary stagecoach drivers. The age-old custom was a popular tradition in the early days of Yard House as guests drank beer from the signature three-foot glass vessel. Today, guests can sip their favorites from the half yard, pint glass, 23-ounce nonic glass and beer samplers.Equal to our passion for what\'s trending in beer is our interest in what\'s cropping up on today\'s innovative menus. Executive Chef Carlito Jocson is always developing new ways to fuse globally inspired flavors with favorite American dishes, giving our menu a worldly yet familiar feel.',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Green Corner Restaurant',website:'greencorneraz.com',address:'1010 W Southern Ave Ste 7',city:'Mesa',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85210',phone:'(480) 835-2313',categories: ['Mediterranean',' Salad',' Greek'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"10:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"10:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"10:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"10:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"10:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"10:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 7:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(1)},
  {name:'Cornish Pasty',website:'cornishpastyco.com',address:'1941 W Guadalupe Rd Ste 101',city:'Mesa',state:'AZ',zipcode:'85202',phone:'(480) 838-3586',categories: ['British'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Cornish Pasties, Salads, desserts, English food, British food',history:'Established in 2009. The Cornish Pasty originates from Cornwall (Southwest England) and can be traced back as far as the 1200\'s. At that time, pasties were baked by wives and mothers of tin miners; which was once a thriving industry in Cornwall. The pasties were made with a thick crimped edge along one side; which the miners would use as a handle and hold onto while eating. This was extremely useful because a miner\'s hand would often be covered in arsenic from the mines. The miners would discard the handle when they were done, so they could never poison themselves while eating. The crusts were never wasted, though, as many miners were believers that ghosts, or "knockers", inhabited the mines. The leftovers of the crusts would keep these ghosts content. The wives and mothers of the miners would make the pasties with different fillings at each end - one with a sweet filling, which would be marked with an initial so the miner would not eat his dessert first, and the other with meat and vegetables.',user: User.find(1)},
