  {name:'City O\' City',website:'cityocitydenver.com',address:'206 E 13th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80203',phone:'(303) 831-6443',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Vegan',' American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Tue":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Wed":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Thu":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Fri":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"9:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)"\}',about:'Vegetarian, vegan, gluten free, pizza, coffee, cocktails, local beers, creative comfort food.',history:'Established in 2007. City, O\' City opened in 2006 as a breakfast, pizza, late night bar. By 2012, it was busting at the seams. We bought the building, more than doubling our space, and re-opened in August 2015.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'WaterCourse Foods',website:'watercoursefoods.com',address:'837 E 17th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80218',phone:'(303) 832-7313',categories: ['Vegetarian',' Vegan',' Comfort Food'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'WaterCourse Foods is a vegan restaurant specializing in delicious and filling comfort food. Our specialties include Banana Bread French Toast, Street Tacos, and Southern Fried Cauliflower "Chicken" served with Mashed Potatoes & Gravy or Mac & Cheese. Along with our seasonal menu, we offer amazing vegan and gluten-free desserts and milkshakes to top off your meal!',history:'Established in 1998. WaterCourse has been a Denver staple since 1998. It was founded as a vegetarian restaurant and updated their menu to entirely vegan in April 2014. Their style of vegan comfort food continues to win over the hearts and stomachs of people from all types of dietary backgrounds.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Sushi Den',website:'sushiden.net',address:'1487 S Pearl St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80210',phone:'(303) 777-0826',categories: ['Japanese',' Sushi Bars',' Bars'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"5:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Wed":"5:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Thu":"5:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Fri":"4:30 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"4:30 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"4:30 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Snooze, an A.M. Eatery',website:'snoozeeatery.com',address:'700 N Colorado Blvd Ste A',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80206',phone:'(720) 677-1973',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sat":"6:30 AM - 4:00 PM","Sun":"6:30 AM - 4:00 PM"\}',about:'Most breakfast & brunch restaurants start with the same script: eggs, batter, coffee & a big ol\' griddle. We\'ve found scripts are a lot like pancakes, they\'re best when flipped, so we\'re always looking to turn the best breakfast classics upside-down & on their side. Stop by for delicious pancakes, french toast, benedicts, breakfast burritos, oatmeal, breakfast sandwiches, bacon & more. From paleo to vegetarian & vegan or dairy free & gluten free friendly, we\'ll happily accommodate food allergies & diets. We want each morning to feel like your weekend & happy hour rolled into one, so our restaurants feature a full bar with alcoholic beverages. From mimosas to bloody marys, margaritas & local craft beers, we\'ve got cocktails & brews covered.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Viewhouse - Centennial',website:'viewhouse.com',address:'7101 S Clinton St',city:'Centennial',state:'CO',zipcode:'80112',phone:'(303) 790-8440',categories: ['American (Traditional)',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Sports Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Tue":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Wed":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Thu":"11:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Fri":"11:00 AM - 2:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"10:00 AM - 2:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)"\}',about:'Viewhouse is a chef-driven, casual eatery, bar and rooftop that delivers a superior, inclusive experience with a locally rooted vibe and fun energy. The original Viewhouse was first conceptualized in 2010 and inspired by Coloradan\'s fondness of sports, love for the outdoors and living a healthy lifestyle revolved around food, activities and all things local. Viewhouse Ballpark opened its\' doors March 2013 in the thriving Ballpark neighborhood of Denver, CO. across from Coors Field and quickly became one of "America\'s Most Popular Bars 2014" via Foursquare. The second view house location opened in Centennial, CO. near the Denver Tech Center in August 2014 with similar aesthetics of the original location, plus new added components, like more rooftop dining and the largest LED T.V. Screen in Colorado, perfect for unparalleled Game-Day watching. Each Viewhouse location promises a vibrant atmosphere, animated staff, indoor and outdoor flatscreen and a variety of bar activities, catering to the city\'s biggest sports fans, backyard game junkies and casual diners alike. Come enjoy the Viewhouse Experience - enriching your life with great eats, views and fun.',history:'Established in 2014. The original ViewHouse was first conceptualized in 2010 & inspired by Coloradan\'s fondness of sports, love for the outdoors & living a healthy lifestyle revolved around food, activities & all things local. ViewHouse Ballpark opened its\' doors March 2013 in the thriving Ballpark neighborhood of Denver, CO across the street from Coors Field & quickly became one of "America\'s Most Popular Bars 2014" via FourSquare. The second ViewHouse location opened in Centennial, CO near the Denver Tech Center in August 2014 with similar aesthetics of the original location, plus new added components, like more rooftop dining & one of the largest LED TV screens in Colorado - perfect for unparalleled game day watching.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Jelly',website:'eatmorejelly.com',address:'600 E 13th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80203',phone:'(303) 831-6301',categories: ['American (New)',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Coffee & Tea'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM"\}',about:'If you\'ve ever experienced food envy, you understand the FOMO associated with an endless menu of delicious items to choose from. This is a common occurrence at Jelly Cafe. Serving up specialties like Maui hot browns and savory French toast, it\'s almost impossible to avoid wandering eyes. Our made-from-scratch kitchen has been known to cause feelings of deep satisfaction while simultaneously spurring insatiable cravings among excited guests. Join us for a good time as you take in the sweet, sweet nectar that is Jelly Cafe.',history:'Established in 1876. Jelly was conceived by partners Josh Epps and Christina Smith, when they moved to Denver in early 2000\'s from San Francisco. "we spent years trying new places out, and were just never satisfies" say Epps. Sure there are good places for brunch, but your either gonna pay a fortune or wait a lifetime, we wanted to create a neighborhood place, were locals go when the get around to scraping themselves out of bed" says Smith. We both come from design backgrounds and creating the look of the place was really the easiest part, Josh had been holding onto a C3po\'s cereal box for years, only to pull out every now and then to show visitors. "We were discussing the art on the walls, what it would be and the thought of having rotating artist on the wall was terrifying, people bringing in their sketches or whatever all the time, im not a gallery owner I dont want to have to tell you its crap so we searched around on ebay and over time, we got a pretty respectable collection together.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'5280 Burger Bar - Denver',website:'5280burgerbar.com',address:'500 16th St Ste 160',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 825-1020',categories: ['Burgers',' American (Traditional)',' Sports Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'t 5280, our mission is to serve you the freshest, all natural ingredients available. We make our buns, and churn our ice cream, from scratch, every day, right here in house. We only serve the finest Colorado Beef, never ever treated with hormones or antibiotics and our produce is selected from the finest local and regional farms',history:'Established in 2014.Conceived by two guys who simply love great burgers, 5280 Burger Bar opened its doors in the Downtown Denver Pavilions to offer the best gourmet, hand-crafted burgers and house made ice creams in the area.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'La Loma | Denver',website:'lalomamexican.com',address:'1801 Broadway Unit 116',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 433-8300',categories: ['Mexican',' Tex-Mex'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'We are an award winning, fine dining Mexican restaurant, formerly located in a distinctive, historic Denver home built in 1887. A Denver tradition for many years, La Loma offers a unique environment with award winning family recipes. Happy Hour 3-6 pm every Monday through Friday! La Loma provides a variety of solutions for your special occasion including semi-private and can accommodate intimate dinners to large parties. We also offer a variety of catering options. La Loma offers brunch every Saturday and Sunday from 11am-3pm.',history:'Established in 1973. The former location was structured out of three mining homes from the late 1800s. These homes were united together to create the Colonial, the Victoria, and the Cantina. We recently relocated to the heart of downtown Denver across the street from the historic Brown Palace Hotel. Evolving somewhat over the years, we offer a "Tex-Mex" menu combining authentic Mexican recipes with flavors from the southwest, and continue to serve many of the same award winning recipes as we did the day we opened, including our famous green chile.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Four Friends Kitchen',website:'fourfriendskitchen.com',address:'2893 Roslyn St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80238',phone:'(303) 388-8299',categories: ['Southern',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sat":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM","Sun":"6:30 AM - 2:30 PM"\}',about:'Southern inspired contemporary American comfort food for breakfast, lunch, and brunch A modern twist on grandma\'s cooking with a great mix of healthy options and indulgences Breakfast and lunch basics plus awesome signature Southern dishes The only rooftop patio option in or near Central Park Full bar with fun cocktail menu and many beers Kid friendly Amazing and unique atmosphere We host private events including baby showers, wedding receptions, corporate parties, birthdays, and many more',history:'Established in 2015. It all began one day when four Stapleton friends (and next-door neighbors) wanted to take their families to a good brunch that was in the neighborhood and family friendly. Realizing the options with those qualities were limited, the four friends began hatching a plan, and with a lot of love and patience, Four Friends Kitchen was born. In just a few months, Four Friends Kitchen has received glowing reviews from the Denver Post, 5280, Westword, Zagat, Eater Denver, and many others.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Syrup Downtown',website:'syruprestaurant.com',address:'999 18th St Ste 105',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(720) 708-5957',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 1:45 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 1:45 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 1:45 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 1:45 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 1:45 PM","Sat":"7:30 AM - 1:45 PM","Sun":"7:30 AM - 1:45 PM"\}',about:'Syrup in Downtown Denver is a locally owned and operated restaurant that puts a modern twist on breakfast, brunch and lunch with 3 locations in the Denver metro area. Join us for your next meal!',history:'Established in 2012. Owner Tim Doherty started infusing maple syrup in his home before launching Syrup, and we\'ve been creating tasty flavors, and amazing dishes ever since. You can always count on us having our signature flavors but stop in today to try our seasonal flavors and specials too.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Osteria Marco',website:'osteriamarco.com',address:'1453 Larimer St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 534-5855',categories: ['Italian',' Pizza',' American (New)'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Work & Class',website:'workandclassdenver.com',address:'2500 Larimer St Ste 101',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80205',phone:'(303) 292-0700',categories: ['American (New)',' Latin American',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"Closed","Wed":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"5:00 PM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"5:00 PM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"5:00 PM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Work & Class is a casual restaurant and bar with the concept of a square meal, a stiff drink, and a fair price. The menu includes roasted, braised, and rotisserie meats, specialty sides, and freshly baked breads and tortillas, along with an interesting selection of beers, wines, and small-batch spirits.',history:'Established in 2014. Work & Class was founded in 2014 by Dana Rodriguez, and Tony Maciag.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'ViewHouse Ballpark',website:'viewhouse.com',address:'2015 Market St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80205',phone:'(720) 878-2015',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Beer Bar'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Tue":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Wed":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Thu":"11:00 AM - 2:00 AM (Next day)","Fri":"11:00 AM - 2:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"10:00 AM - 2:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)"\}',about:'ViewHouse is an independently owned & chef-driven eatery, bar & rooftop with 4 locations in Denver, Centennial, Littleton, & Colorado Springs open daily for lunch, happy hour, dinner, late night, takeout, delivery, weekend brunch, & offers free events, fitness classes, music, entertainment, private events, banquets, & catering. ViewHouse is not only a dining destination - it\'s an experience known for great eats, views, & fun. ViewHouse sources 100+ local products & serves a Colorado-centric selection of 35 local taps, 15 local distilleries, & 40 house-made cocktails. ViewHouse is committed to making a positive impact by sourcing local, partnering with hundreds of local neighboring organizations, & continually giving back to the community.',history:'Established in 2013. The original ViewHouse was first conceptualized in 2010 & inspired by Coloradan\'s fondness of sports, love for the outdoors & living a healthy lifestyle revolved around food, activities & all things local. ViewHouse Ballpark opened its\' doors March 2013 in the thriving Ballpark neighborhood of Denver, CO across the street from Coors Field & quickly became one of "America\'s Most Popular Bars 2014" via FourSquare. ViewHouse Centennial opened in 2014 followed by ViewHouse Littleton in 2017, and ViewHouse Colorado Springs in 2020.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Guard and Grace',website:'guardandgrace.com',address:'1801 California St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 293-8500',categories: ['Steakhouses',' Seafood',' American (New)'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Fri":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"4:00 PM - 9:30 PM"\}',about:'Guard and Grace is a modern steakhouse by Chef / Owner Troy Guard, with locations in Denver and Houston. On our menu, you\'Äôll find quality ingredients, innovative combinations, and an emphasis on wood-fired dishes.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Angelo’s Taverna',website:'angelosdenver.com',address:'620 E 6th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80203',phone:'(303) 744-3366',categories: ['Italian',' Seafood',' Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'Pizza Oysters on the half shell Char-Grilled Oysters Ravioli Pasta',history:'Established in 1974. Angelo\'s has been a popular pizza destination for over years in a great Denver neighborhood on 6th Ave. Run by the Laveo family until March of 2013, when Eric Hyatt and Craig Jones bought the restaurant and it\'s recipes to continue the tradition of delicious Italian food but with a new, oyster twist! The two long time friends are proud to serve Angelo\'s favorite dishes alongside fresh new options, such as Arancini, Calamari, homemade pastas, seafood and char-grilled oysters! With an excellent wine menu and at tentative staff, Angelo\'s is excited to continue a Denver tradition.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'True Food Kitchen',website:'order.truefoodkitchen.com',address:'2800 E 2nd Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80206',phone:'(720) 509-7661',categories: ['American (New)',' Vegetarian',' Vegan'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"10:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'True Food Kitchen is a restaurant and lifestyle brand inspired by the philosophy that food should make you feel better, and that great tasting food and thoughtfully crafted beverages can serve as the foundation for a life well lived. True Food\'s seasonal menu is guided by the principles of Dr. Andrew Weil\'s anti-inflammatory food pyramid and emphasizes wholesome, simple ingredients with simple preparations to highlight the natural health benefits and flavors of each ingredient. From nutrient-dense staples and carefully sourced proteins to little-known superfoods, True Food Kitchen is committed to sourcing the most responsible, creative, in-season ingredients.',history:'Established in 2008. Founded in Phoenix, Arizona, in 2008, True Food Kitchen is a restaurant and lifestyle brand inspired by the philosophy that food should make you feel better, not worse, and that great tasting food and thoughtfully crafted beverages can serve as the foundation for a life well lived. True Food Kitchen emphasizes wholesome, simple ingredients with simple preparations to highlight the natural health benefits and flavors of each ingredient.',user: User.find(9)},
