  {name:'Denver Biscuit Company',website:'denbisco.com/broadway',address:'141 S Broadway',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80209',phone:'(303) 377-7900',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Sandwiches',' Coffee & Tea'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Fogo De Chao Steakhouse - Denver',website:'fogodechao.com',address:'1513 Wynkoop St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 623-9600',categories: ['Brazilian',' Steakhouses'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Tue":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Wed":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Thu":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Fri":"11:30 AM - 2:00 PM,5:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Fogo de Chão is an internationally-renowned steakhouse from Brazil that allows guests to discover what\'s next at every turn. Founded in Southern Brazil in 1979, Fogo elevates the centuries-old culinary art of churrasco - roasting high-quality cuts of meat over an open flame - into a cultural dining experience of discovery. Please join us in our dining room, in our more casual Bar Fogo, or bring the Fogo Experience to you with Fogo To-Go or Catering. Visit our website to make a reservation or place an order.',history:'Established in 1979. Fogo de Chao is a leading Brazilian steakhouse, or churrascaria, which has specialized in fire-roasting high-quality meats since 1979 utilizing the centuries-old Southern Brazilian cooking technique of churrasco.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Lucile\'s Creole Cafe',website:'luciles.com',address:'275 S Logan St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80209',phone:'(303) 282-6258',categories: ['Cajun/Creole',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Coffee & Tea'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 2:00 PM"\}',about:'Cajun Creole Breakfast and Lunch',history:'Established in 1980. For more than forty years, Lucile\'s has been a staple among Colorado residents and visitors, serving delicious creole dishes inspired by the flavors and culture of New Orleans. Lucile\'s has been owned and operated by the same family since the restaurant\'s inception in 1980, and has grown from a small eatery in downtown Boulder to more than six locations in the greater Denver area, from Littleton to Longmont. As a family establishment, we always strive to provide a comfortable and unique atmosphere, in addition to excellent food. Come try some of our famous dishes like the "Cajun Breakfast" (red beans, poached eggs, hollandaise and grits) and our "Eggs New Orleans" (fried eggplant, poached eggs, creole spice and hollandaise) - start your meal with some of our melt-in-your-mouth beignets, or fluffy, buttery biscuits. From our family to yours. Lucile\'s is proud of our reviews on Yelp, so feel free to do research before you try us! We promise you won\'t be disappointed.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Jax Fish House LoDo',website:'jaxfishhouse.com',address:'1539 17th St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 292-5767',categories: ['Seafood',' American (New)',' Live/Raw Food'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"3:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"3:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"3:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"3:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"3:30 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"3:30 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"3:30 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'We don\'t take ourselves too seriously at Jax Fish House. Two things we do take seriously? The freshness and sustainability of our seafood. You know fresh fish when you see, smell, and taste it--and thanks to modern delivery technology, we bring in that freshy-fresh seven days a week. Sustainability is a little more complicated. Not all commercial fisheries are created equal. That\'s why we work closely with our suppliers and science-based organizations to ensure that every single thing we serve is responsibly sourced. We consider the stocks of the species we source to prevent overfishing and we work with suppliers who harvest in ways that have minimal impacts on marine environments.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Tacos Tequila Whiskey',website:'tacostequilawhiskey.com',address:'1514 York St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80206',phone:'(720) 475-1337',categories: ['Mexican'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'D Bar Denver',website:'dbardenver.com',address:'494 E 19th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80203',phone:'(303) 861-4710',categories: ['Desserts',' American (Traditional)',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"Closed","Wed":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"10:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"10:30 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'D Bar is the home of Denver\'s favorite Desserts. Grab a treat, coffee or espresso from our Pastry Shop (same blag-entrance on 19th Ave) or cozy up to the dessert bar and watch talented pastry chefs create imaginative plated desserts!',history:'Established in 2008. The original D Bar Denver opened its doors May 24, 2008 as a 28 seat "mom and pop" restaurant. Today there are two locations: 494 E 19th Denver and 3930 5th Ave in San Diego, CA! D Bar #3!? Let\'s see where our sweet future takes us!',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'The French Press',website:'myfrenchpress.com',address:'15290 E Iliff Ave',city:'Aurora',state:'CO',zipcode:'80014',phone:'(303) 369-3111',categories: ['Cafes',' Coffee & Tea',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"6:30 AM - 3:00 PM","Tue":"6:30 AM - 3:00 PM","Wed":"6:30 AM - 3:00 PM","Thu":"6:30 AM - 3:00 PM","Fri":"6:30 AM - 3:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'Homemade breakfast and lunch made to order. Locally roasted fair-trade organic coffee.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Buckhorn Exchange',website:'buckhornexchange.com',address:'1000 Osage St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80204',phone:'(720) 507-2162',categories: ['Steakhouses',' American (Traditional)',' Wine Bars'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"5:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"5:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"5:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"5:00 PM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"4:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Sat":"4:00 PM - 9:30 PM","Sun":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'The Buckhorn Exchange is located in the city\'s oldest neighborhood, just 5-minutes from downtown Denver. This National Historic Landmark and Western Museum has been serving the finest in Old West fare since 1893. Prime grade beef steaks, buffalo prime rib, elk, salmon, quail, game hen, and succulent baby-back pork ribs are just some of the marvelous offerings on the Buckhorn menu. Exotic appetizers such as alligator tail, rattlesnake and buffalo sausage are available, and no dinner is complete without the house specialty, Rocky Mountain Oysters. For lunch we serve up a lighter fare including our renowned Grandma Fanny\'s pot roast sandwich, enormous beef and buffalo burgers, bratwurst or rib platters, main course salads, and the Buckhorn\'s famous bean soup. For dessert, the hot Dutch apple pie ala mode with cinnamon rum sauce, or the double-chocolate Rocky Road brownie are sinful experiences that will forever remind you of your visit to the one and only Buckhorn Exchange.',history:'Established in 1893. Now in its second century of operation, The Buckhorn Exchange, which has liquor license Number One in the State of Colorado, was founded on November 17, 1893 by Henry H. "Shorty Scout" Zietz, easily recognized as one of the most colorful figures of the Old West. The Buckhorn Exchange derives its name from the Rio Grande Railroad yards that were directly across Osage Street and the second-story Buckhorn Lodge that housed railroaders for the night. Each Friday, the railroaders scrambled across Osage Street to exchange their paychecks for gold. In return, Zietz handed each man a token good for a free lunch and a beer. A great deal has changed at the Buckhorn since 1893, yet much is as it was in the days when the clientele packed six-guns, silver barons rubbed elbows with roustabouts, miners shook dirt out of their clothing along with gold dust, and "Shorty Scout" entertained the customers with tales of the decade he spent on the frontier.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'The Bagel Deli & Restaurant',website:'bageldeli.com',address:'6439 E Hampden Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80222',phone:'(303) 756-6667',categories: ['Delis',' Bagels',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"8:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Tue":"8:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Wed":"8:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Thu":"8:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Fri":"8:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 4:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 4:00 PM"\}',about:'Attitude; Corned Beef; Pastrami; Lox; Bagels; Cream Cheese; Chopped Liver; Familiar Faces; Rye Bread; Chicken Soup; Matzo; Challah; Friends; Kosher Salami; Giant Hot Dogs; Cheesecake; Rugulach; Knowledge; Brisket; Matzo Balls; Kreplach; Tradition, especially Tradition.',history:'Established in 1967. Rhoda\'s parents, Paul and Lola Weiner, bought The Bagel in 1967. The first store was on 14th Ave. at Krameria. The store on Hampden was opened in 1971 and the two ran concurrently for over 30 years. We closed 14th about 8 years ago. We\'ve proudly served Denver over 40 years. Many of our employees have worked well over 20 years and several have worked since the early 1970\'s. Ask Shirley about her days as a cashier, or Bill as a dishwasher...just a couple of our mainstays at the deli.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Yak and Yeti Restaurant and Brewpub',website:'theyakandyeti.com',address:'7803 Ralston Rd',city:'Arvada',state:'CO',zipcode:'80002',phone:'(303) 431-9000',categories: ['Indian',' Himalayan/Nepalese',' Breweries'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'The Yak and Yeti Restaurant and Brewpub is a full-service restaurant featuring fine Indian food along with handcrafted beer made right on the premises. You will love our delicious food and comfortable atmosphere, suitable for the entire family, but also special enough for just that certain someone. In Nepal & India, food is an art form that has been passed on from generation to generation, from guru (teacher) to vidhyarthi (pupil). Our cuisine is as rich and diverse as Nepalese & Indian civilization, encompassing a vast scope of traditions and regional variations in taste, color, texture, appearance, and delicacy. The hospitality of Nepalese & Indian people is also legendary. In Sanskrit literature there are three words that form the motto of Nepalese & Indian hospitality: "Atithi Devo Bhava," meaning "your guest is your god." Food is the crown of festivals and celebrations, and whatever the occasion, Nepalese & Indians eat with great gusto. Yak and Yeti Restaurants are open seven days a week. Come visit us today.',history:'Established in 2008. Yak and Yeti Restaurant and Brewpub has been serving residents of Arvada, Colorado since 2008. Our mission is to delicious Indian food with an emphasis on customer satisfaction. With over 13 years in business, we look forward to adding you to our list of happy customers.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Hops & Pie',website:'hopsandpie.com',address:'3920 Tennyson St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80212',phone:'(303) 477-7000',categories: ['Pizza',' Beer Bar',' Sandwiches'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:30 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"12:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"12:00 PM - 8:00 PM"\}',about:'We serve delicious crafts beers and fresh artisan pizzas. Hops & Pie takes pride in serving local Colorado craft beer, but we also serve craft beer from all over the nation and the world. Try our artisan pie of the month, or make your own pizza with our fresh toppings. We also offer wheat and gluten free crust, and have a myriad of vegan and vegetarian toppings, as well as other vegan and vegetarian dishes on our menu. As great as our pizzas are, we also offer other options, like our IPA Mac & Cheese, Chipotle Mango Carnitas Tacos, fresh salads, and delicious sandwiches. Ask about joining our Beer Club. It\'s like a never ending happy hour! Also, make sure to join us for happy hour Tuesday - Friday from 3:00 - 6:30 p.m.',history:'Established in 2010. After a combined 23 years in the fine dining scene all across the country, we decided it was time to slow life down a little bit and do our own thing, and what better thing than pizza and beer? While living in San Diego, the idea of Hops & Pie was born. Partially inspired by living in close proximity to Stone, Lost Abbey, Port, Green Flash and Ballast Point Breweries, we began to develop a love for hand crafted beer. We soon learned that good IPA and pepperoni pizza were made for each other. That inspired us to start creating different pies to see how they paired with different beers, and we soon learned that the sky was the limit. So we packed up, moved to the Napa Valley of beer, and started looking for a home for Hops & Pie. We were lucky to find a space on Tennyson in the Berkeley neighborhood of Denver. It took a little over six months to design, build, and open up. And here we are, bringing North Denver our idea of the perfect combination: craft beer and artisan pizza.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'FelFel Mediterranean',website:'eatfelfel.com',address:'4401 S Tamarac Pkwy',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80237',phone:'(303) 586-5540',categories: ['Mediterranean',' Seafood',' Kebab'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'It\'s been said that good food makes people happy. It\'s been proven that exceptional food makes people healthy. At FelFel, we set the standard for Mediterranean cuisine. We believe it\'s possible for a meal to be nutritious without compromising the delicious factor. You will notice a difference in the quality of our ingredients from the first bite to the last savory morsel. Your taste buds will thank you. And you can thank us by telling a friend about your experience.',history:'Established in 2013. It\'s been said that good food makes people happy. It\'s been proven that exceptional food makes people healthy. At FelFel, we set the standard for Mediterranean cuisine. We believe it\'s possible for a meal to be nutritious without compromising the delicious factor. You will notice a difference in the quality of our ingredients from the first bite to the last savory morsel. Your taste buds will thank you. And you can thank us by telling a friend about your experience.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Harley\'s A Hot Dog Revolution',website:'harleysdogs.com',address:'1500 W Littleton Blvd Ste 112',city:'Littleton',state:'CO',zipcode:'80120',phone:'(720) 236-9617',categories: ['Hot Dogs',' American (Traditional)'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Tue":"Closed","Wed":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 8:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 4:00 PM"\}',about:'We have a great variety of gourmet hot dogs. From a pastrami dog, bbq brisket dog and rare roast beef dogs to spicy guacamole dogs even pizza dogs! We are about 90% homemade and have quite a following! Come check us out!',history:'Established in 2013. Harley\'s grew out of Southwest Plaza Mall and created a buzz that continues to this day. Family run and operated, it continues to delight young and old with it\'s homemade flair and appeal. Harley\'s offers original meals that you simply can\'t find anywhere else. You can see from the reviews that people love it at Harley\'s!',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Appaloosa Grill',website:'appaloosagrill.com',address:'535 16th St Ste 110',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(720) 932-1700',categories: ['American (New)',' Bars',' Steakhouses'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Tue":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Wed":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Thu":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Fri":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"11:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"11:30 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)"\}',about:'Established in 2001, The locally owned Appaloosa Grill is a refreshingly unique choice amongst the vast choice of typical eateries that line the 16th St. Mall. There is always an owner in the building and the no matter the time of the day Appaloosa Grill has adapted itself to fit the greatest neighborhood needs for both locals and visitors alike. Appaloosa also runs a 3,300sf banquet facility on the second floor known as the Wright Room - please visit wrightroom.co',history:'Established in 2001. Once a feather in Governor John Hickenlooper\'s cap the Appaloosa Grill was purchased by its management team in 2005 and has become a neighborhood favorite location for visitors and locals alike. The Grill has always served all natural proteins and made most everything from scratch right down to the ketchup. For over 13 years the Appaloosa has provided live music for your heart and soul every single night of the year for free!',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Ophelia\'s Electric Soapbox',website:'opheliasdenver.com',address:'1215 20th St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 993-8023',categories: ['Bars',' Breakfast & Brunch',' Venues & Event Spaces'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"5:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Tue":"5:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Wed":"5:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Thu":"5:00 PM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Fri":"5:00 PM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sat":"10:00 AM - 1:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)"\}',about:'Upscale 8000 Sq. Ft. Gastrobrothel Features Justin Cucci, of Root Down and Linger\'s Vegetable Forward, Globally-Inspired Dishes and a Live Music Venue \'Electric Soapbox.\' Ophelia\'s is a restaurant, bar, and live music venue, with a boudoir-style décor that honors the building\'s past, and Ophelia, the muse. Continuing the Edible Beats tradition of delicious, responsibly-sourced food, the upscale, gastrobrothel-inspired menu will include fresh, craveable takes on flatbread pizza, small plates, burgers, and shareable charcuterie boards. Simple, handcrafted cocktails with fresh, local ingredients as well as kegged cocktails and a tap draft line featuring all-Colorado beers.',history:'Established in 2015. Ophelia\'s has taken many forms: located in the historic 1894-era Victorian Airedale building, it was a brothel, turned peep show, turned adult video library. The building, which is also on the National Register of Historic Places, will house Ophelia\'s, the latest project of Justin Cucci and the Edible Beats team.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Ocean Prime',website:'ocean-prime.com',address:'1465 Larimer St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 825-3663',categories: ['American (New)',' Seafood',' Steakhouses'],price:'$$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"4:00 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"4:00 PM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Nationally acclaimed, modern American restaurant and lounge known for its stunning settings, impressive menu of seafood and steak, and private dining options.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Tocabe, An American Indian Eatery',website:'tocabe.com',address:'3536 W 44th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80211',phone:'(720) 524-8282',categories: ['American (Traditional)',' Desserts'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"12:00 PM - 8:00 PM"\}',about:'Tocabe, An American Indian Eatery brings a new and exciting concept to Denver\'s restaurant community. A local, privately owned restaurant, Tocabe specializes in contemporary American Indian cuisine, combining traditional Osage family recipes with elements of modern Native American fare. Tocabe\'s fast casual style offers diners eat-in and take-out, along with catering options to meet your needs.',history:'Established in 2008. Tocabe has been deeply involved in the local community for years and takes pride in their commitment to both the local and Native American communities. The restaurant\'s setting is a clean, warm, open space with connections to American Indian cultural elements infused with a contemporary atmosphere.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Hopdoddy Burger Bar',website:'hopdoddy.com',address:'1747 Wynkoop St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 446-2337',categories: ['Burgers',' American (Traditional)',' Beer Bar'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:30 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:30 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:30 PM"\}',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Highland Tap and Burger',website:'tapandburger.com',address:'2219 W 32nd Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80211',phone:'(720) 287-4493',categories: ['Burgers',' Sports Bars',' Chicken Wings'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:30 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:30 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"10:00 AM - 12:00 AM (Next day)","Sun":"10:00 AM - 11:00 PM"\}',about:'The Highland Tap & Burger is a casual neighborhood restaurant and bar that has been a part of the Highlands community for over 10 years. Our seasonal menu is designed to satisfy your appetite using only the best ingredients, so whether you\'re dining on one of our traditional American classic burgers or balling out on fois gras and Wagyu beef, you\'ll leave feeling satisfied. Our year-round patio is pet friendly, so bring your furry friends for a pint and a bite! We feature 18 TVs, so every seat in the house is a good one. We also have every sports package and are happy to put your game on - just ask your server or bartender and we\'ll make it happen for you! Feel free to book reservations on our website, or contact our events coordinator for more information on large parties, catering, and The Bungalow, our secret hideaway for special events. See you at The Tap!',history:'Established in 2010. The Highland Tap and Burger was created by 3 former Michiganites Kevin Eddy, Kris Slocum and Paul Brown and 3 former Bostonians Brad Beale, Katie O\'Shea and her Husband Juan Padro. The partners have over 60 years in the food and beverage industry. Our Idea was to find a growing, thriving neighborhood in the Denver metro area that would fit our concept of a restaurant/bar that serves local craft brews, gourmet burgers, signature sandwiches, appetizers, salads, soups prepared with as many locally grown ingredients as possible. The "Tap" will broadcast professional and college sports NFL, NCAA, NHL, NBA and MLB on 16 50 inch TV\'s. The Lower Denver Highlands or "LoHi" fit our objective perfectly. The owners of the "Tap" are proud of the LoHi neighborhood and will be participating in community and charity events as well as bring new ideas to the LoHi area. The Tap welcomes everyone to share and comment and help make our new establishment grow and thrive along with the neighborhood.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Angelo\'s Taverna',website:'angelostaverna.com/littleton',address:'6885 S Santa Fe Dr Ste A',city:'Littleton',state:'CO',zipcode:'80120',phone:'(720) 532-1389',categories: ['Italian',' Pizza'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:30 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:30 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'We are continuing a tradition of great food and welcoming hospitality! We are shucking the freshest oysters, delivered daily! Varieties from the East and West coasts will surely satisfy your bivalve cravings. Try our unique Char-grilled oysters as well. Served hot and bubbling with our signature sauces, our char-grilled oysters are sure to please even a non-oyster eater.',history:'Established in 2016. Angelo’s has been a staple on Sixth Avenue since 1974. It was owned and operated by the Laveo family until March of 2013, when Craig Jones and Eric Hyatt bought it and kept the old world family recipes adding modern twists, such as char grilled oysters and balsamic glazed ribs, to make the eclectic menu that you see today. Now, three years into its rebirth, Angelo’s is thriving in the same neighborhood, boasting Denver’s best happy hour and an oyster bar that moves over 7000 oysters a week, ensuring the freshest from both coasts.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Seoul Korean BBQ & Hot Pot',website:'seoulkoreanbbq.com',address:'2080 S Havana St',city:'Aurora',state:'CO',zipcode:'80014',phone:'(303) 632-7576',categories: ['Korean',' Barbeque',' Hot Pot'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'All dishes are served with 14 side dishes when you order the meal or Barbeque combination.',history:'Established in 2007. 2009 west word reward 2010 west word reward 2012 west word reward 2013 west word reward 2014 west word reward',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Urban Egg Denver Tech Center',website:'urbaneggeatery.com',address:'6991 E Belleview Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80237',phone:'(720) 482-4070',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' American (Traditional)',' Sandwiches'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 2:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 2:30 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 2:30 PM"\}',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Onefold',website:'onefolddenver.com',address:'1420 E 18th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80218',phone:'(303) 954-0877',categories: ['Breakfast & Brunch',' Cafes'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sat":"8:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"8:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'We are breakfast restaurant that carries locally sourced and organic ingredients, everything is hand made in house from our organic flour tortillas to our bone broths. We also carry coffee that is locally roasted. Dine in or to go.',history:'Established in 2015. We just opened in March',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'The Corner Office Restaurant + Martini Bar',website:'thecornerofficedenver.com',address:'1401 Curtis St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80202',phone:'(303) 825-6500',categories: ['American (New)',' Lounges'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 11:00 PM"\}',about:'The Corner Office, downtown Denver, is simply great food and outstanding cocktails. Designed with good times and comfort in mind, the bustling bar and energetic dining rooms feature retro-chic interiors infused with intrigue. Progressive global comfort food mixed with international flavors give traditional favorites a fresh twist.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'The 49th',website:'the49thdenver.com',address:'4550 S Kipling St Ste 6',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80127',phone:'(720) 255-2021',categories: ['Burgers',' Bars',' Seafood'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'The 49th specializes in Alaska inspired comfort food and cocktails. Fish & chips featuring wild Alaskan cod, salmon, & seasonal halibut, elk-beef blend burgers, and a selection of creative starters, salads, & entrees as well as weekly specials. Brunch available on the weekends.',history:'Established in 2014. The 49th is a cozy spot inspired by my upbringing & adventures in Alaska. Long winters, short summers & a sense of adventure best describe the 49th state and we aim to recreate that rugged & carefree spirit here in Colorado. Swing by with old friends, make some new ones, and enjoy Alaskan inspired food & drinks in a friendly & casual neighborhood setting! Cheers, Josh',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Los Chingones Denver',website:'loschingonesmexican.com',address:'2463 Larimer St',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80205',phone:'(303) 295-0686',categories: ['Mexican'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'Los Chingones is Chef Troy Guard\'s take on "badass" Mexican-sassy, spicy, sometimes irreverant, always an adventure',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Shells and Sauce',website:'shellsandsauce.net',address:'2600 E 12th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80206',phone:'(303) 377-2091',categories: ['Italian',' Bars',' Salad'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"Closed","Tue":"3:30 PM - 8:30 PM","Wed":"3:30 PM - 8:30 PM","Thu":"3:30 PM - 8:30 PM","Fri":"3:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Sat":"3:30 PM - 9:00 PM","Sun":"Closed"\}',about:'Serving authentic Italian American food in the heart of Congress Park, Shells and Sauce brings Old Country taste to a cozy neighborhood restaurant. If you\'re craving homemade lasagna, meat or fish, Shells and Sauce has a variety of savory appetizers and entrees to choose from. We also boast an extensive wine list to pair with anything you choose, and we offer delicious desserts to top off your evening. Join us for Happy Hour! Happy Hour is Tuesday-Sunday from 3-6 PM.',history:'Established in 2007. We have also recently added another patio, on the roof! Enjoy a fantastic view of the Congress Park neighborhood while sipping on a glass of wine and enjoying your favorite pasta combinations.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Torchy\'s Tacos',website:'torchystacos.com',address:'1085 N Broadway',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80203',phone:'(303) 436-1704',categories: ['Tex-Mex',' Tacos'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"10:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"9:00 AM - 10:00 PM"\}',about:'At Torchy\'s, we\'re serious about one thing. And one thing only. Our food. We source the highest quality ingredients around so we can serve up the best damn taco (or salad) you\'ve ever tasted. Cooked to order--just the way you like it.',history:'Established in 2006. Torchy\'s Tacos was founded in 2006 in Austin, Texas, when a man with a dream bought a food trailer and a vibrant red Vespa. Mike Rypka, founder of Torchy\'s Tacos, built a menu out of experimental tacos that were coined by fans as "Damn Good." By living the Damn Good mantra, Torchy\'s Tacos is always innovating to deliver the most unique tacos, award-winning queso and refreshing margaritas in the taco game, including the Taco of the Month, an untraditional taco offering that keeps our taco fans coming back for more.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'North Italia',website:'northitalia.com',address:'190 Clayton Ln',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80206',phone:'(720) 941-7700',categories: ['Italian',' Pizza',' Cocktail Bars'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 10:00 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 11:00 PM","Sun":"11:00 AM - 9:00 PM"\}',about:'At North Italia, we\'re passionate about more than just our crave-worthy Italian food menu. We put our all into every detail, creating an environment that lets you know you\'re in for something special. Every day there is a new delicious favorite made from scratch, like our Chef\'s daily pizzas, waiting to be discovered and devoured. A tempting assortment of wines, beer, and house-made cocktails give you endless ways to treat yourself. From the moment you walk through our doors, to your last scoops of budino at the end of a satisfying meal, you\'ll know you\'re in good hands.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Rosenberg\'s Bagels & Delicatessen',website:'rosenbergsbagels.com',address:'725 E 26th Ave',city:'Denver',state:'CO',zipcode:'80205',phone:'(720) 440-9880',categories: ['Delis',' Bagels',' Breakfast & Brunch'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Tue":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Wed":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Thu":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Fri":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sat":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM","Sun":"7:00 AM - 3:00 PM"\}',about:'As stated by the New York Times, "Former Jersey Boy, Joshua Pollack has taken the quest for a decent New York-style bagel west of the Mississippi to heroic heights". Through figuring out how to replicate the New York City water that makes their bagels one-of-a-kind, Joshua and his Rosenberg\'s family provide you with soft and chewy, right out of the oven bagels, fish smoked and cured in house, delicious salads, high end coffee, pastries and oh, so much more!',history:'Established in 2014. After months of construction and years of product development, we opened the doors of Rosenberg\'s Delicatessen to the public on July 26, 2014. Named after the Owners Mother and guardian angel, Karen Rosenberg Pollack, Rosenberg\'s Deli is rooted in the two things we are most passionate about - food and family.',user: User.find(9)},
  {name:'Sushi Katsu',website:'sushikatsudenver.com',address:'2222 S Havana St Ste H',city:'Aurora',state:'CO',zipcode:'80014',phone:'(303) 368-8778',categories: ['Sushi Bars',' Japanese'],price:'$$',hours:'\{"Mon":"11:00 AM - 2:30 PM,4:30 PM - 9:30 PM","Tue":"11:00 AM - 2:30 PM,4:30 PM - 9:30 PM","Wed":"11:00 AM - 2:30 PM,4:30 PM - 9:30 PM","Thu":"11:00 AM - 2:30 PM,4:30 PM - 9:30 PM","Fri":"11:00 AM - 2:30 PM,4:30 PM - 10:00 PM","Sat":"11:00 AM - 2:30 PM,4:30 PM - 10:00 PM","Sun":"12:00 PM - 8:30 PM"\}',about:'Our business specializes in delicious sushi. We have the best all-you-can-eat sushi in town which all of our 20 sushi chefs are proud of! Every sushi is made when you put in the order, so its fresh and delicious! We serve nearly 800 people a day so our fish never sits in our cooler for longer than 24 hours!',user: User.find(9)},
